description:
At Modo Energy, we're on a mission to build the information architecture for the energy transition - we want to be the only place to come to for information on the global journey to net zero. Take a look at our platform, where we provide open access to an array of content on the energy transition.

We're a dedicated and passionate team building a category-defining business, working on one of the world's most important priorities. We are looking for individuals who love product-building, want to work with pace at a mission-oriented startup, and will collaborate with us in shaping the culture of a rapidly growing team.

The role

The Market Analyst will have experience within the sector and a desire to use their knowledge and expertise to help produce novel, industry-standard research and analysis to support customers and the wider battery energy storage sector.

On top of this, they will be working in collaboration with Modo's data, modelling, and product teams to help plan and build data analytics products that will revolutionise the workflow of others across the power industry.

Modo Energy tools are used to help organisations finance, build, benchmark, and operate battery energy storage systems. Therefore, this role represents an opportunity for the successful candidate to become a highly influential thought leader within the space.

You will have a huge influence on the company (and, by extension, the industry) as we expand our research and product offerings within Australia and the wider APAC region. And you will be helping to build a product that every market participant uses.

Responsibilities:


 * Producing data-led, analytical content about power markets and asset operations, in a variety of formats - but mainly written articles and videos - to communicate high-value insights to our audience.
 * Being a founding member of Modo's Australian office, supporting operations and new hires, and helping to establish office culture.
 * Staying up to date with the latest news across markets and policy, communicating this within the company and to the wider industry.
 * Getting to know our users, building your network, and staying up to date with the latest developments in the clean energy industry.
 * Working collaboratively with teams across the business, to make sure that all aspects of the organisation are pulling in the same direction and giving our users huge value across all of our product, content, and customer-facing endeavours.
   
   

Qualifications:


 * 2+ years of professional working experience in power markets.
 * In-depth knowledge of how the electricity system works and how power is traded - preferably with some experience of how battery energy storage systems earn money - in the NEM.
 * Excellent quantitative and analytical skills. You'll be relied upon to discover, explore, visualize, and communicate trends and patterns you find in numerical data, in ways that provide value to our users.
 * Experience in writing clearly and concisely - to distill and communicate complex topics into accessible, jargon-free language.
 * Strong critical thinking skills. At Modo Energy, you will have the platform to become an influential thought leader within the renewable energy space - but you'll need to be able to develop your own thoughtful opinions, and ask insightful questions of those around you (internally and externally).
 * Nice to have:
    * Experience carrying out complex data analysis in Python.
      

Important Details:


 * We work in a Hybrid Environment: You split your time between working from home and working in our Sydney (Business District) office (Tuesday - Thursday).
   
   

Modo Energy is an equal opportunity employer. Our employment decisions are made on the basis of qualifications, merit and business need. We do not discriminate against age, national origin, physical or mental disability, race, religion, pregnancy, sexual orientation, gender identity, veteran status or any other characteristic protected by federal, state, or local law. If you need assistance or a reasonable accommodation with an application or the interview process please contact us via email at careers@modo.energy.

What you can expect from Modo

We want to attract and retain the best talent at Modo, and we give our people the freedom and opportunity to develop themselves and flourish.

We are committed to building a diverse and inclusive team at Modo, as we believe a variety of backgrounds, skills and interests is what makes our company stronger. If you share our values and our enthusiasm for supporting the transition to greener energy systems, we encourage you to apply. We have a number of positions open which could be for a range of backgrounds and experience levels. Please get in touch if you are interested and you don't meet all the requirements, or if you exceed them!
title: Market Analyst

description:
About the Business




LexisNexis Risk Solutions is the essential partner in the assessment of risk. Within our, Business Services vertical, we offer a multitude of solutions focused on helping businesses of all sizes drive higher revenue growth, maximize operational efficiencies, and improve customer experience. Our solutions help our customers solve difficult problems in the areas of Anti-Money Laundering/Counter Terrorist Financing, Identity Authentication & Verification, Fraud and Credit Risk mitigation and Customer Data Management.

You can learn more about LexisNexis Risk at the link below, https://risk.lexisnexis.com/.




About our Team




You will be part of a team of analysts using global data from the largest real-time fraud detection platform to optimise solutions for our enterprise customers.




About the Role




You will use your experience with data analysis to investigate suspicious behaviour. This will provide new insights to customers leading to immediate real-world impact in the form of fewer scam victims, lower consumer friction, reduced fraud losses and as a result, increased customer profitability.

You’ll leverage a real-time platform analyzing billions of transactions per month for some of the largest companies operating in Financial Services, Insurance, e-Commerce, and On-Demand Services. These tools will allow you to attain a unique perspective of the Internet, and every persona connected to it. You’ll be continually collaborating with internal product and engineering teams, customer-facing account teams, and external business leaders and risk managers. The comprehensive policies you build will go head-to-head against some of the most motivated attackers in the world to protect billions in revenue.




This is a permanent full-time role based in Melbourne office with home-based arrangement.




Responsibilities




· Conducting in-depth reviews of complex fraud cases. identifying trends and actionable insights, documenting your findings and making clear recommendations on how to mitigate risk

· Using your SQL and Python skills to increase our customers’ fraud capture. While reducing false positives, conducting offline analysis of customer data to expose patterns and statistically tune policies. Produce executive-level reports and own the end-to-end delivery of your recommendations by writing rules into the ThreatMetrix® decision engine

· Building dashboards & reports to track value delivered by the solution. Increasing focus on more bespoke external-facing dashboards that surface the most important insights to each customer

· Using your excellent attention to detail and ability to craft a story through data. Delivering industry-leading presentations for external and executive audiences with non-technical background

· Scoping, planning, and delivering customer-focused projects including root cause analysis, reports, dashboards, rule mining and health checks. Demonstrate a professional and customer-centric persona when interacting directly with customers via phone, e-mail, and chat

· Collaborating with ThreatMetrix teams. Including Products, Engineering, Sales and other Professional Services colleagues around the world to continually redefine best practices




Requirements




· Demonstrate knowledge of Python and SQL (BI tools such as SuperSet, Tableau or PowerBI is a bonus)

· Have attention to detail to ensure quality of project delivery for customers stands out amongst industry peers

· Track record of building external and executive reports and presentations

· Interest or experience in consulting within the risk, fraud or payments industry. Experience of working with fraud system management, such as ThreatMetrix, Emailage, Featurespace, Hunter, Iovation, BioCatch, Actimize Falcon, etc

· Have extensive multi-tasking and prioritization skills. Needs to excel in fast paced environment with frequently changing priorities

· Demonstrate fluency in English. Any other languages spoken across APAC are a bonus, particularly Japanese.

Learn more about the LexisNexis Risk team and how we work here




We are looking to fill this role as soon as possible – apply now to be considered.




Thank you for your interest

About Us

At ubank, we want to empower the digital generation to be more successful with money. Think of us more as a daily money companion. One that brings together the ability for customers to see their money in one place, with smart features and real-time insights designed to help them get ahead.

With ubank, our customers can discover what it feels like to save more, see exactly where they’re spending and own their own home faster. In short, we want to help them achieve real momentum with money.

Your why

You are a driven data professional with a passion for using insights to drive smarter decision making and an improved customer experience. But you also aren’t afraid to roll up your sleeves to do some building. You are excited by the opportunity to work with cutting-edge technology and want to play a key role in the transformation of analytics and insights delivery for a rapidly-growing, digitally-native business.

How You Will Spend Your Time

What You Will Bring

Essential

Why Ubank?

Hybrid working model - with 3 days in our central Sydney CBD office located above Wynyard station.

Highly collaborative and positive culture

Strong internal development & growth opportunities

Our Values

description:
In Australia, Dabble has been operating a licensed sportsbook under the NTRWC since 2021. We're here to deliver extraordinary - with a truly immersive socialised betting experience designed to provide evolutionary entertainment to our punters via genuine interaction and engagement.

We have office hubs in Darwin, Melbourne, Brisbane, Sydney, Adelaide, and Albury. While we support remote-friendly work, we also encourage our people to take advantage of our national network of offices, offering cross-office sponsored flights year-round to promote collaboration and connection.

Our global operations span multiple markets, including our innovative Daily Fantasy Sports app servicing the United States, which launched in 2023.

We are a team of highly driven enthusiasts and we are looking for our next Dabbler to join us as we continue in our journey.

Dabble Culture


 * Dress for your day so you can focus on what matters
 * Switch up your office, work from home, work from wherever helps you to deliver
 * Genuine, like-minded team of visionaries. We welcome ideas big and small!
 * Scheduled focus time to encourage deep thought
 * Our annual convention, Dabblecon, brings us all together to celebrate our successes and plan continued evolution over the coming year
 * Each day is led through upholding our core Values: Fun, Celebratory, Community, Evolutionary and Focus
   

Dabble Perks

 * A minimum of five weeks of paid annual leave for all Dabblers
 * Paid parental leave for both primary and secondary caregiver
 * We encourage you to visit our network of offices: sponsored flights available to staff and spouse/immediate family
 * Flexibility with working hours to accommodate our cross-country employee base: you are free to manage your own time
 * Your wellness is our genuine concern: We sponsor access to the Sonder app for employees and their families with 24/7 support across mental health, medical advice, safety support and
   more
 * Up to 10% annual cash bonus based on Company performance metrics
 * Dabble Day Dividend: all Dabblers split the day’s revenue evenly on our birthday each year. You share the workload, why shouldn’t you share the reward?
 * Safety first: your ride home from company sponsored events and your flu jab is on us

Overview


The Business Intelligence Analyst will play a crucial part in analysing the interplay between social and transactional activities, crafting advanced analytics solutions to support all facets of our business.??

Your responsibilities will span from collaborating with stakeholders to harnessing data-driven insights to driving strategic decisions. You will support the design, implementation, and delivery of business intelligence, reporting and data analysis to answer wide varying questions presented to you from across the business.?

Responsibilities?

 * Collaborate with business stakeholders to develop and maintain insightful dashboards for key operational functions, including Risk & Trading, Finance, Customer Operations, Compliance, and Marketing?

 * Continuously enhance functional reporting to ensure accuracy and agility in alignment with our growing business needs?

 * Write and revise complex SQL code to ensure efficient query performance?

 * Conduct regular trend analysis on customer preferences and engagement methods to identify opportunities to adapt our business strategy model?

 * Source and transform data to provide insight to unique market leading product opportunities?

 * Perform ad-hoc analysis, investigations and data management tasks as required by stakeholders?

 * Analyse the distribution of generosities and promotions including determination of true generosity and promotion cost, as well as identify who should obtain, and in what frequency to reward and reactivate users at a cost-efficient way to the business?

 * Collaborate with the data engineering team to inform optimal data models for enhanced query performance?

 * Ensure data reliability & accuracy through internal processes?
   

Skills & Qualifications?

 * A degree or qualification within a relevant technical discipline?

 * Proficient in Microsoft Excel with the ability to utilise advanced analytical techniques?

 * Basic skills in a Business Intelligence tool like Power BI, Tableau or AWS Quicksight??

 * Experience with databases and SQL Language essential (1 year)??

 * High level of initiative, strong attention to detail and excellent interpersonal and communication skills (both verbal and written)?

 * Strong analytical and problem-solving abilities??

 * Ability to prioritise and concurrently work through a variety of stakeholder requests and at any point in time?

 * An understanding of the wagering industry is preferred, but not required?


Primary Location

This role is currently open to all locations within Australia.


Are you a Dabbler?

A Dabbler’s attitude is paramount, as the right person will be able to learn quickly and adapt to any skill gaps. A Dabbler is always a team player, with a willingness to share with and learn from others. Being a remote-first workplace, collaborative working styles are crucial to empower and grow each individual member (eg we prefer openness via public channels to problem solve or ideate on Slack).


A Dabbler uses their freedom of autonomy to its absolute potential and enjoys contributing to the Dabble community. We hold respect for our peers very highly – there is no such thing as a bad idea. We encourage you to think differently, be brave and strive to always raise the bar. Dabble was born out of thought sharing and should tackle growth in the same way. Dabble embraces empowerment of all people at any level of seniority and experience to ‘own their work’ and ‘talk their book’ wherever they can.

A fulfilling life extends beyond work, and we encourage our employees to prioritise self-care and well-being. This means taking breaks when needed, setting boundaries, and seeking support when facing challenges. We are committed to creating a safe environment where individuals feel comfortable discussing their wellbeing and accessing resources when necessary.


Remuneration

The advertised salary for this position is $90,000 - $120,000 + Super + Benefits with room to be flexible.

 * Support the data store in identifying and revising reporting requirements.
 * Support initiatives for data integrity and normalisation.
 * Assess tests and implement new or upgraded software. Assist with strategic decisions on new systems. Generate reports from single or multiple systems.
 * Troubleshoot the database environment and associated reports.
 * Identify and recommend new ways to streamline business processes.
 * Organising data into usable formats.
 * Assessing data quality and cleaning data.
 * Team culture – contributing to a collaborative, agile, curious analytic team?.
 * Establishing productivity systems and processes – providing input into processes and systems (e.g., DevOps and Git) to manage work and share code.
 * Innovative approaches – advocate for, and pioneer, novel approaches to delivering data migration.
 * Work with departmental managers to outline the specific data needs for each business process.
 * Create efficient and reusable SQL code meant for the improvement manipulation and analysis of data.
 * Create efficient and reusable code. Follows coding best practices.
 * Create reports depicting the trends and behaviours from analysed data.
 * Create documentation for worked performed. Additionally, perform peer reviews of documentation of others' work.
   
   

Required Skills And Experience


 * Data mapping, Data transformation and Data migration experience.
 * Database languages such as SQL.
 * Programming language such as R or Python.
 * Analytical tools and languages such as SAS & Mahout is an advantage.
 * Efficiently with spreadsheet tools such as Microsoft Excel or Google Sheets.
 * DBMS.
   
   

Benefits & Perks


 * Flexible/hybrid working arrangements.
 * Health insurance.
 * Novated Car Lease.
 * Access to UST Perks (Reward Gateway), which offers discounts across major retailers.
   
   

Our commitment to Diversity, Equity and Inclusion

Diversity and Inclusion are among the founding blocks of how UST as an organisation translates its values of Humility, Humanity, and Integrity into practice.

About UST

For more than 25 years, UST has worked side by side with the world's best companies to make a real impact through digital transformation. Together, with over 35,000 employees in 30+ countries, we build for boundless impact—touching billions of lives in the process.

title: Data Analyst

description:
12 Months Max Term Contract

Engage with complex data and drive meaningful change

Leverage your expertise to transform analytics into meaningful strategic recommendations

Tennis Australia is embarking on a phase of Digital Transformation, and as a result, an opportunity has emerged for a Data Analyst. The Digital Transformation Program will establish new digital experiences, foundational capabilities and strategic enablers. Unified Digital Experience will cover Web and Mobile Digital Presence for Tennis Australia. This digital experience will enhance how our customers find courts, coaches and tournaments, participate in Leagues and Tournaments, manage their rating and ranking, and administrators and deliverers who organise and deliver Tennis.

If you need assistance or adjustments to participate in the application process fully, please contact recruit@tennis.com.au.

About The Role

Join Tennis Australia as an experienced Data Analyst and help transform complex datasets into actionable insights that drive business decisions. In this role, you'll utilise tools like SQL, Python/R, and Web Analytics to create reports and dashboards that inform stakeholders and executives. Collaborate closely with various teams to unlock the value of data and support a culture of data-driven decision-making across the organisation.

In this role, you will:

Data Analytics - Support the delivery of digital analytics, mapping, code/error management, and scripting to assist internal stakeholders and initiatives.


 * Understand the use of Google Cloud Platform (GCP), Google Marketing Platform tools, SEO, web crawlers, and other resources that facilitate digital analytics.
 * Monitor, track, and develop dashboards and benchmark reports based on stakeholder requirements
 * Understand and establish data models that shape digital analytics capabilities.
   
   
   

Development of Customer Insights and Data Library -Develop tools and reports to monitor key performance indicators across the enterprise


 * Analyze customer data using cloud tools to create large data sets.
 * Generate and present fact-based customer and product performance insights to improve engagement and personalization models.
 * Combine data from various sources to generate insights.
   
   
   

Data Analysis - Improve decision-making by applying market knowledge to influence strategic direction.


 * Create advanced data models to solve complex issues and provide insightful analyses.
 * Translate data insights into actionable recommendations, presenting information clearly and persuasively.
   
   
   

Customer Analytics, Marketing Automation and CRM - Utilize modern data science and machine learning techniques within a CRM context.


 * Create dashboards and reports to generate actionable insights.
 * Use analytics to enhance CRM marketing strategies, focusing on profitability, lifetime value, loyalty, and ROI.
 * Develop predictive capabilities for segmentation and modelling to improve customer retention and acquisition.
 * Design target groups for CRM campaigns and help the marketing team optimize testing by analysing campaign performance across customer segments.
   
   
   

About You

What you will bring to the role:


 * Strong capabilities in time management, planning, and prioritisation.
 * Extensive hands-on knowledge and experience with tools and techniques for analysis, data manipulation, and presentation (such as SQL, web analytics tools, Python, data visualization, and web/app design and coding).
 * Ability to adapt to cloud technologies and systems for managing and manipulating data analytics across diverse channels.
 * Experience in database analysis and data extraction techniques.
 * Excellent communication skills, able to translate and communicate data insights into actionable business recommendations for a diverse audience.
 * Proven experience in working to derive valuable insights, as well as visualizing these insights for both technical and non-technical stakeholders.
 * Ability to maintain composure under pressure while working in a dynamic and challenging environment.
 * A strong curiosity to analyse data and translate findings into business insights and recommendations.
 * Demonstrates initiative, recommends best practices, and determination to ensure the fulfilment of goals.
 * Effective collaboration within a team environment
 * You must hold (or be willing to obtain) a current Police Check and Working with Children Check.
   
   
   

What’s in it for you?


 * Career development with a range of formal education and on-the-job training opportunities
 * Tickets to the Australian Open
 * Monthly health & wellbeing activities through our Thrive program.
 * Onsite gym & tennis facilities
 * Flexible working practices
 * Free car parking
 * A range of discounts from our sponsorship partners
   
   
   

To Apply

If you think you’re up to the challenge, we’d love to hear from you! A copy of the position description can be found here. Please submit your resume and cover letter via our online application system. Please note, only applications that include a portfolio will be considered.

Tennis Australia is committed to providing a safe environment for all tennis participants, including children and young people. It is essential everyone involved with delivering tennis in Australia understands their responsibility in relation to child-safety.

We believe playing makes life better and we are always on the lookout to talented people to join our team and help us create a playful world through tennis.

Even if we are not currently advertising the position that you are looking for today, we may be tomorrow. There are a number of ways that you can keep up-to-date with new opportunities as they happen.

We encourage you to create a profile and register for our job alerts, as well as follow Tennis Australia on LinkedIn to stay up to date on the latest news and opportunities.
title: Data Analyst

description:
Reliance Worldwide Corporation (RWC)

Plumbing Matters. We make it better. Our innovative products, built on a tradition of excellence, serve markets across plumbing, heating and construction to make our customers’ lives easier, while sustainably delivering unrivalled returns. We are publicly listed on the Australian Stock Exchange (ASX) and headquartered in Atlanta, Georgia, USA with regional headquarters in Brisbane, Australia and London, UK. Our global family of trusted brands is committed to making a positive, lasting impact – we are better for our planet and better for our people. We operate in 45 facilities across 20 countries. We’re acquisitive and we’re laser-focused on growth.

In 2024 Holman Industries joined the RWC brand powerhouse In Australia. The Holman innovative spirit is stronger than ever – bringing 66 years of heritage from the watering and gardening sector together with a decade of plumbing expertise.




Together, we’re constantly looking ahead at new applications and challenges, from sustainability to the changing needs of the modern built environment, to how we can continue to make lives easier and safer for the next generation.




Our Culture

We’re big enough to make a difference and small enough for each one of us to make an impact. Our culture encourages our people to think differently, challenge the status quo and shape the world around us. Our values drive how we work together, as one global team. We have something special here – not just what we do, but who we are. We're not afraid to try new things; we punch above our weight; and we move with speed. We embrace governance but reject bureaucracy or anything that slows us down. Our strategy ensures we provide a safe environment for our people and we actively promote diversity and inclusion. Everyone at RWC makes a valuable contribution to our business. Sound like somewhere you could call home? Read on.




Eagle Farm Location

 * Newly created role to lead strategic plans, budgets, forecasts and financial results
 * Finance Business Partner to the sales team
 * Be part of a global and industry-leading organisation with an ambitious growth strategy
 * Generous salary package up for grabs




Are you looking for a role where you can partner with senior leaders to influence the direction of the business in an ASX-listed global organisation with an ambitious growth strategy? Are you curious about market dynamics, competitors and customers? Are you an analyst with scrupulous attention to detail and committed to continuous improvement? Then we would love to hear from you.




About the role:

This is a newly created role in the Asia Pacific region to drive positive change. Reporting to Financial Planning & Analysis Manager, we are looking for a dynamic analyst who can help lead a positive change program, this position depends on strong business partnerships and clear communication with senior leadership and will participate in financial planning and analysis of projects of varying nature and complexity with limited supervision. This may include industry and competition analysis, scenario planning, customer/channel profitability, continuous improvement, and returns on investment.

Based in Eagle Farm in Brisbane, you will be responsible for partnering with the APAC sales team providing reporting, analysis and business insights. This will also include pricing oversight and customer incentive management. At RWC we operate as one global team, so you will be part of a broader group of finance professionals located in the UK and USA.

You will enjoy being innovative and thinking outside the box and be comfortable to respectfully challenge the norm.




What you will need to do:

 * Partner with end users to understand business challenges, and explore and analyse various data sets to provide the right solutions.
 * Develop a fundamental understanding of cross-functional business processes (ERP and other) to support reporting initiatives.
 * Create reports, dashboards, and analyses that cater to the needs of different levels of users in various business functions.
 * Collaborate with the global Business Intelligence team to help influence analytics strategy, develop requirements and design solutions.
 * Provide support to the executive team by developing dashboards, summaries, management reporting, and what-if analyses.
 * Educate and train the user community on Power BI, Business Objects, and the development of SAP Analytics Cloud.
 * Maintain sales reporting, in-stock position, and open order position utilizing BI
 * Update, maintain and communicate key performance indicators to management.




About you:

 * You will bring the highest level of personal integrity and ethics
 * You will be a great team player with a problem-solving attitude
 * Have a commercial mindset and demonstrated high analytical skills and ability to think strategically
 * Be able to roll your sleeves up to get the job done
 * You will hold a relevant bachelor’s degree
 * 8+ years of accounting, finance, or related experience
 * Experience budgeting, forecasting, and reporting.
 * Ability to develop a deep understanding of the business and its key drivers
 * Strong analytical, problem-solving, conceptual, and critical-thinking skills
 * Advanced financial modelling and MS Excel skills (e.g. pivot tables, VLOOKUP’s, sumifs)
 * Manage competing priorities under pressure
 * Basic Knowledge of BI, reporting, data warehousing, cloud infrastructure and analytics concepts
 * Working knowledge of Business Objects Suite and Power BI
 * Experience in SAP Analytics Cloud is a plus
 * Working experience or knowledge of SAP ERP
 * Prior working experience with SAP HANA and modelling is desired
 * Intermediate knowledge of SQL is desired
 * Ability to lead cross-functional meetings and assist in designing and developing content
 * Working closely with users to collect and document business requirements
 * Documenting requirements as user stories that communicate the expectations of the business to the project team, developers, and/or vendors
 * Ability to quickly understand new business data and processes to detect areas of improvement







APPLY NOW! Send a cover letter telling us about you and why this role is the one for you.

description:
In Australia, Dabble has been operating a licensed sportsbook under the NTRWC since 2021. We're here to deliver extraordinary - with a truly immersive socialised betting experience designed to provide evolutionary entertainment to our punters via genuine interaction and engagement.

We have office hubs in Darwin, Melbourne, Brisbane, Sydney, Adelaide, and Albury. While we support remote-friendly work, we also encourage our people to take advantage of our national network of offices, offering cross-office sponsored flights year-round to promote collaboration and connection.

Our global operations span multiple markets, including our innovative Daily Fantasy Sports app servicing the United States, which launched in 2023.

We are a team of highly driven enthusiasts and we are looking for our next Dabbler to join us as we continue in our journey.

Dabble Culture


 * Dress for your day so you can focus on what matters
 * Switch up your office, work from home, work from wherever helps you to deliver
 * Genuine, like-minded team of visionaries. We welcome ideas big and small!
 * Scheduled focus time to encourage deep thought
 * Our annual convention, Dabblecon, brings us all together to celebrate our successes and plan continued evolution over the coming year
 * Each day is led through upholding our core Values: Fun, Celebratory, Community, Evolutionary and Focus
   

Dabble Perks

 * A minimum of five weeks of paid annual leave for all Dabblers
 * Paid parental leave for both primary and secondary caregiver
 * We encourage you to visit our network of offices: sponsored flights available to staff and spouse/immediate family
 * Flexibility with working hours to accommodate our cross-country employee base: you are free to manage your own time
 * Your wellness is our genuine concern: We sponsor access to the Sonder app for employees and their families with 24/7 support across mental health, medical advice, safety support and
   more
 * Up to 10% annual cash bonus based on Company performance metrics
 * Dabble Day Dividend: all Dabblers split the day’s revenue evenly on our birthday each year. You share the workload, why shouldn’t you share the reward?
 * Safety first: your ride home from company sponsored events and your flu jab is on us

Overview


The Business Intelligence Analyst will play a crucial part in analysing the interplay between social and transactional activities, crafting advanced analytics solutions to support all facets of our business.??

Your responsibilities will span from collaborating with stakeholders to harnessing data-driven insights to driving strategic decisions. You will support the design, implementation, and delivery of business intelligence, reporting and data analysis to answer wide varying questions presented to you from across the business.?

Responsibilities?

 * Collaborate with business stakeholders to develop and maintain insightful dashboards for key operational functions, including Risk & Trading, Finance, Customer Operations, Compliance, and Marketing?

 * Continuously enhance functional reporting to ensure accuracy and agility in alignment with our growing business needs?

 * Write and revise complex SQL code to ensure efficient query performance?

 * Conduct regular trend analysis on customer preferences and engagement methods to identify opportunities to adapt our business strategy model?

 * Source and transform data to provide insight to unique market leading product opportunities?

 * Perform ad-hoc analysis, investigations and data management tasks as required by stakeholders?

 * Analyse the distribution of generosities and promotions including determination of true generosity and promotion cost, as well as identify who should obtain, and in what frequency to reward and reactivate users at a cost-efficient way to the business?

 * Collaborate with the data engineering team to inform optimal data models for enhanced query performance?

 * Ensure data reliability & accuracy through internal processes?
   

Skills & Qualifications?

 * A degree or qualification within a relevant technical discipline?

 * Proficient in Microsoft Excel with the ability to utilise advanced analytical techniques?

 * Basic skills in a Business Intelligence tool like Power BI, Tableau or AWS Quicksight??

 * Experience with databases and SQL Language essential (1 year)??

 * High level of initiative, strong attention to detail and excellent interpersonal and communication skills (both verbal and written)?

 * Strong analytical and problem-solving abilities??

 * Ability to prioritise and concurrently work through a variety of stakeholder requests and at any point in time?

 * An understanding of the wagering industry is preferred, but not required?


Primary Location

This role is currently open to all locations within Australia.


Are you a Dabbler?

A Dabbler’s attitude is paramount, as the right person will be able to learn quickly and adapt to any skill gaps. A Dabbler is always a team player, with a willingness to share with and learn from others. Being a remote-first workplace, collaborative working styles are crucial to empower and grow each individual member (eg we prefer openness via public channels to problem solve or ideate on Slack).


A Dabbler uses their freedom of autonomy to its absolute potential and enjoys contributing to the Dabble community. We hold respect for our peers very highly – there is no such thing as a bad idea. We encourage you to think differently, be brave and strive to always raise the bar. Dabble was born out of thought sharing and should tackle growth in the same way. Dabble embraces empowerment of all people at any level of seniority and experience to ‘own their work’ and ‘talk their book’ wherever they can.

A fulfilling life extends beyond work, and we encourage our employees to prioritise self-care and well-being. This means taking breaks when needed, setting boundaries, and seeking support when facing challenges. We are committed to creating a safe environment where individuals feel comfortable discussing their wellbeing and accessing resources when necessary.


Remuneration

The advertised salary for this position is $90,000 - $120,000 + Super + Benefits with room to be flexible.
title: Business Intelligence Analyst

description:
See yourself in our team:



Join our diverse Customer Service Direct (CSD) team where you'll use AI to make banking more accessible and personalised for millions of Australians. Your expertise will help shape inclusive, customer-focused solutions through our banking app, call centres, and digital channels. You will join a balanced, collaborative team who are focused on driving innovation that helps all Australians achieve financial wellbeing.

Do work that matters:

As a Data Scientist, you will be key in helping designing AI solutions that understand and respond to diverse customer needs including building intelligent systems that make banking easier for all community members. You will work on projects that balance innovation with ethical considerations and mentor and collaborate with team members across the organisation. This will include working with modern ML frameworks and tools, cloud computing platforms and Enterprise-grade AI infrastructure.

We support our people with the flexibility to balance where work is done with at least half your time each month connecting in office. We also have many other flexible working options available including changing start and finish times, part-time arrangements and job share to name a few. Talk to us about how these arrangements might work for you.

We are seeking people who have:


 * Ability in solving complex problems with creative solutions
 * Skills in building consensus and collaborating across teams
 * Experience in translating technical concepts for various audiences
 * Passion for creating inclusive, user-friendly solutions
   
   

Technical Skills:


 * Proven experience in: Python, Spark, SQL, or equivalent programming languages
 * Background in developing or deploying AI/ML models
 * Knowledge of Generative AI applications
 * Familiarity with AWS, GitHub, or similar platforms
   
   

Working with us

Whether you’re passionate about customer service, driven by data, or called by creativity, a career with CommBank is for you.

Our people bring their diverse backgrounds and unique perspectives to build a respectful, inclusive, and flexible workplace. One where we’re driven by our values, and supported to share ideas, initiatives, and energy. One where making a positive impact for customers, communities and each other is part of our every day.

Here, you’ll thrive. You’ll be supported when faced with challenges and empowered to tackle new opportunities. We really love working here, and we think you will too.?


 * Apply Now to live your best life, by doing your best work with us! **
   
   

If you're already part of the Commonwealth Bank Group (including Bankwest, x15ventures), you'll need to apply through Sidekick to submit a valid application. We’re keen to support you with the next step in your career.

We're aware of some accessibility issues on this site, particularly for screen reader users. We want to make finding your dream job as easy as possible, so if you require additional support please contact HR Direct on 1800 989 696.

Advertising End Date: 18/12/2024

A rare opportunity to gain exposure to Generative AI!

Location: Sydney with office attendance 3 days per week

Skills & Experience:

 * 5+ years Business Analyst experience
 * Prior regulatory reporting and data transformation project experience as a Business Analyst
 * Intermediate SQL, including reconciliation of data across data platforms

title: Data Business Analyst - Banking

description:
About the Role:

Are you passionate about transforming data into actionable insights that drive meaningful change? Join our dynamic Research and Analytics team, where your expertise will directly shape customer experiences and business success. If you enjoy uncovering trends, crafting compelling narratives, and delivering value through data, this is the opportunity for you!

As a Data Analyst, you’ll work with cutting-edge technologies and collaborate with cross-functional teams to deliver impactful solutions. Your work will drive innovation, refine processes, and contribute to strategic decision-making in a supportive and collaborative environment.

If you were here yesterday, here are some things you would have been involved in:


 * Gathered data from multiple sources, such as databases and spreadsheets.
 * Conducted exploratory data analysis (EDA) to identify trends, patterns, and outliers.
 * Transformed and prepped data for analysis, including normalisation and encoding.
 * Designed visually engaging dashboards and reports using tools like Tableau or Power BI.
 * Presented key findings to stakeholders through concise reports and compelling visualisations.
 * Maintained comprehensive documentation to ensure reproducibility and transparency.
   
   
   

Keen to get involved? You’ll just need some of the following:


 * Proficiency in programming languages including SQL, Python, R, DAX and M.
 * Experience with data analysis tools including Excel, Parsehub, Power Query, Power Automate and visualisation tools such as Power BI and Tableau (Desirable)
 * Strong analytical skills and a keen eye for detail.
 * Excellent communication skills to share insights with technical and non-technical audiences.
 * A degree in Data Science, Computer Science, Engineering, or a related field
 * Minimum of 2 years’ experience with MS Power Platform in an enterprise environment
 * Experience consuming data from data warehouses and other sources.
 * IT Enterprise experience and B2B IT Market Segmentation models desirable.
   
   
   

The Kinetic Difference:


 * Flexible working, paid parental leave, and other benefits tailored to your individual goals.
 * Regular fun company and social events
 * Vendor Exam Support, ITIL V4 Training and Communities of Practice groups
 * Dedicated professional development reviews every 6 months, with monthly follow ups
 * An open and supportive culture where we respect all people and individuals, and everyone has a voice
   
   
   

About Kinetic IT:

Kinetic IT has come a long way since opening its doors, growing to become one of Australia’s largest ICT managed service providers with over 1400 staff. With offices in all major capitals, we support customers with complex ICT infrastructures, critical data and multi layered environments – and we don’t limit ourselves to a single industry or sector.

It’s safe to say we’re not your typical IT outsourcer – we’re privately owned and make looking after our people and culture a priority (which is why we’re recognised as an employer of choice). Every day our people come to Kinetic IT not just to work, but to be challenged, grow, and just say ‘hi’ to their friends

How To Apply

First, check out our website Kineticit.com.au. If you like what you see then, click on the ‘Apply Now’ button or contact our career account on careers@kineticit.com.au.
title: Data Analyst

description:
At EY, you’ll have the chance to build a career as unique as you are, with the global scale, support, inclusive culture and technology to become the best version of you. And we’re counting on your unique voice and perspective to help EY become even better, too. Join us and build an exceptional experience for yourself, and a better working world for all.

Data Analyst

What if we didn’t focus on who you are now, but who you could become?

At EY we believe that whoever you are, your uniqueness helps us stand apart.

We bring together extraordinary people, like you, to build a better working world.

What’s in it for you?

As a Consultant Data Analyst you’ll be responsible for contributing to the delivery of processes, solutions and/or projects. You’ll design dashboard and analyses to be performed, identify trends and patterns, and be accountable for delivering work and meeting targets which impact the immediate team. You will also:


 * Work with other data & analytics professionals to optimise, refine and industrialise analysis into solutions
 * Determine relevant data and sources, and collect, organise and process data to analyse
   
   

What We’re Looking For

Here’s our ‘wish list’ but don’t worry if you don’t tick all the boxes. We’re interested in your strengths, what you want to learn, and how far you want to go.


 * Demonstrated intermediate knowledge of tools used in the design and build of data analysis and interpretation solutions
 * Foundational knowledge of the techniques and tools to develop data structures
 * Foundational understanding of data mining tools, technologies, methods and techniques applied to big data streams and the dynamic characteristics of big data
   
   

What We Can Offer You


 * Explore how a career at EY is yours to build at www.ey.com/au/careerdevelopment
 * Discover how, when and where you can work at www.ey.com/au/flexibility
 * Learn about our commitment to DE&I at www.ey.com/au/diversity-inclusiveness
 * Discover the various ways our benefits can cater to your needs, across wellness, financial wellbeing, and family-friendly policies which include 26 weeks gender neutral paid parental leave at www.ey.com/au/benefits
 * We offer a competitive salary which is open to negotiation pending on skills and experience.
   
   

Acknowledgement of Country

EY acknowledges the Traditional Owners and Custodians of the lands on which EY offices are located around Australia. We pay our respects to their cultures, and to their Elders — past, present, and emerging. Find out more about our vision for reconciliation at www.ey.com/au/reconciliation

Apply now… we’re over 9,000 perspectives in Australia and we’re ready to welcome yours.

description:
Are you a motivated, resilient and committed data professional with data management, reporting and analysis skills and expertise? Are you passionate about supporting Queensland government to deliver exceptional services driven by data-enabled policy setting and decision making? Bring your high-level technical skills and methodical and collaborative work style to the Data and Analytics team in DTET, and help us to contribute to the important work of supporting businesses and training Queenslanders now and into the future.

Working closely with the Manager, Business Intelligence and Customer Reporting (BICR), the Senior Data Analyst contributes to the maintenance, development and implementation of various performance reporting methods and systems to monitor and project performance data pertaining to the topics of employment, small business and vocational education and training (VET).

About The Role

As the Senior Data Analyst you will


 * Extract, analyse, interpret and present complex data sets for distribution to internal and external clients in response to on-demand requests and annual reporting requirements.
 * Develop and maintain cloud-based business intelligence and data visualisation solutions to present departmental data and statistics in an accessible and userfriendly manner for distribution to internal and external clients.
 * Develop and maintain data collection processes in accordance with departmental standards and procedures.
 * Provide technical assistance and expert advice to staff on data-related projects and the appropriate use, interpretation and presentation of data.
 * Maintain knowledge of best practice data management techniques to ensure data presentation and sharing meets customer needs.
 * Liaise with other departmental officers, other government departments and the wider community to manage expectations, gain a broader knowledge of user needs/desires and to identify data sharing opportunities.
   
   
   

What We Are Looking For

The position requires an applicant who has:


 * Demonstrated ability in managing the collection, extraction, analysis, interpretation and reporting of complex data sets in a cloud-based environment to a high standard within tight timelines.
 * Demonstrated ability to participate in a work team and to interact professionally with a wide range of stakeholders.
 * Demonstrated professionalism and integrity in dealings with stakeholders, management and work colleagues.
 * Demonstrated high-level oral and written communication skills to contribute written analysis and visuals to reports, research papers, Ministerial, briefing papers and other information in the context of fostering evidence-based policy development, with the capacity to understand the audience and tailor your communication style.
 * Demonstrated ability to work flexibly across multiple projects and activities and manage competing priorities.
   
   
   

It is highly desirable for applicants to possess a bachelor's degree or higher in data science, statistics, mathematics, engineering, or similar quantitative field - or have at least two years' experience in a similar data analytics role.

Refer to the Role Description for a full list of responsibilities and what we are looking for.

How To Apply

To apply, please submit the below via the SmartJobs application page:


 * Your current resume
 * Provide a short statement (maximum 1 page) telling us why you are interested in this role, outlining what your motivation is to join us.
   
   
   

Please ensure you refer to the Role Description 'Interested in applying' section for more information on what to include as part of your application. We're committed to appointing the best-suited person for each role. This includes considering equity, diversity, respect, and inclusion needs within our agency. We believe that these elements are essential for the success of our team, and we strongly encourage applicants from diverse backgrounds to apply. If you require any reasonable adjustments to fully participate in the recruitment process, please do not hesitate to reach out to the designated contact for the vacancy.

Applications to remain current for 12 months.

description:
Country Road Group (CRG) is embarking on transformation to position itself for growth, leveraging our scale, capabilities and culture as a House of Brands. We are investing in new and existing capabilities and have a number of exciting opportunities available.

 

The Sustainability Data Analyst is responsible for coordinating data collection activities across the group relating to environment, human rights and ethical sourcing and community partnerships. This role reduces regulatory and legal risk by maintaining accurate and assurable datasets through controlled collection, collation, storage and management processes, and delivers accurate and insightful sustainability reporting that enables effective decision-making by CRG stakeholders.

 

The Sustainability Data Analyst will lead data science and reporting activities to create insights and support CRG’s regulatory reporting obligations and will proactively work to strengthen CRG’s data systems. 

 

Key Accountabilities

 

 * Collect, analyse and interpret environmental and social sustainability data across CRG (e.g. energy, packaging, ethical sourcing, community partnership impact and donations) 
   

 * Undertake data cleansing as required and ensure that data sets are accurately maintained 
   

 * Lead data science and reporting activities to create insights and support CRG’s regulatory reporting obligations 
   

 * Prepare reports and dashboards on business sustainability performance and product sustainability substantiation, highlighting key insights and trends 
   

 * Support the evolution of our Good Business Journey by providing decision-useful data insights and trends 
 * Support the delivery of key internal and external sustainability disclosures, including annual WHL and APCO packaging reporting, modern slavery statement and upcoming climate disclosures (AASB S2), as well as ad hoc external reporting requirements 
 * Support the claims substantiation process by maintaining and updating the key data points relating to styles, purchase orders and PLM attributes in the centralised claims validation reconciliation report 
   

Key Capabilities 

 

 * Bachelor degree in Science, Sustainability, Applied Data Science or Information Technology (completed or in the process of completing)
 * Experience in data analysis for sustainability or other business-wide non-financial datasets. 
 * Familiarity with sustainability reporting (e.g. Global Reporting Index) and carbon accounting frameworks (e.g. NGERS, GHG Protocol) desired.  
 * Experience with Scope 3 GHG emissions data capture and analysis highly favourable. 
 * Proficiency in Microsoft reporting software, including Excel and Power BI 
 * Familiarity with common analysis software tools, including SQL databases 
 * Strong communication skills, with clear understanding of the needs of different stakeholders and report audiences 
 * Strong analytical and critical thinking skills with a strong eye for detail 
 * Excellent organisational and time management skills 
 * Has a passion for sustainability and driving positive outcomes
   

Why work for CRG?

 

The Country Road Group is one of Australasia’s largest Lifestyle Brand Houses comprising of iconic brands such as Country Road, POLITIX, Trenery, Witchery and MIMCO. Here are some of the great things we offer:

 

 * Generous employee discounts across our House of Brands
 * Seasonal clothing allowance
 * An additional day of leave for your birthday
 * An Industry leading Parental Leave Program
 * Flexible working arrangements to support work/life balance
 * Annual learning calendar to support the ongoing development of our team
 * Support community partnerships across our Corporate Social Responsibility Program
 * We are committed to operating ethically, sustainably, and responsibly.

 * Career growth via succession planning, internal promotions, and mentorship opportunities
 * Ongoing investment in professional development through industry certifications and study assistance
 * Mental health support through our Employee Assistance Program
 * Support for family and caring responsibilities, including paid parental leave.
 * Employee referral program, with monetary incentives offered.
   
   

What Our People Say:

“Atturra has a great working environment and management are very supportive of their staff. We celebrate success and have fun while working hard.”

What You’ll Be Doing

Atturra’s Data & Analytics practice combines Atturra capabilities and key partnerships to take the lead in consulting and solutions across the data, analytics and AI spectrum. Using all forms of data and the right analytics, we help clients realise greater agility and resilience by increasing confidence in the decisions they make. This allows our clients to improve business performance using solutions that combine human expertise with smart technology.

This role will involve leveraging analytical techniques to help our clients make better decisions with their data. Depending on what a particular client needs, we make use of business intelligence tools such as Power BI; statistical and data science approaches including machine learning; all the way through to AI, bespoke algorithms and large-scale cloud computing approaches. In this role you will be able to add to your existing skillset and experience, with your work playing an integral role in tackling real problems.

This opportunity is based in Sydney and ideally requires an NV1 Australian Government security clearance, but Australian citizenship as a minimum and an openness to obtaining the required clearance. You will also be expected to spend several days each week on site at RAAF Glenbrook in the Blue Mountains.

What will make you successful in this role?

Success In This Role Will Require You To Either Possess Characteristics Like Those Listed Below, Or To Have a Strong Interest In Developing Them:


 * A passion for taking on interesting and impactful real-world problems using analysis to drive better data-driven decision-making
 * Quantitative skills from fields such as mathematics, statistics, data science, actuarial, economics, engineering, or the classical sciences
 * Experience with platforms including Power BI (intermediate to advanced use), Visual Studio, MS SQL Server Management Studio, Azure DevOps, Git will help you standout for the initial piece of work we have in mind.
 * Skills with Tableau, Microsoft Azure, Wolfram Language / Mathematica, Python or R may also be advantageous for later opportunities
 * Strong communication skills and the ability and desire to work in close collaboration with diverse groups of Atturra peers and clients
 * A willingness to learn from and collaborate with our Atturra experts and our clients on challenging problems across a range of industries
 * Security clearance to work on Australian federal government and defence projects is highly desirable; but in the absence of this, Australian citizenship and a willingness to apply for relevant security clearances.
   
   

How To Apply

Careers | Atturra

https://atturra.com/au-en/careers

Recruitment Agencies/Headhunters:

We got this covered. Our Talent Acquisition team is working on our hiring demands and will reach out should we need extra support. Atturra only accepts referrals from agencies on our official supplier list via Agency Portal. Agencies are required to go through our procurement process, have an approved fee agreement, and be invited to participate in hiring for a job opening by the Atturra Talent Acquisition team. Any profiles or referrals submitted outside of this process will be deemed invalid. We request that you do not contact Atturra employees outside of the Talent Acquisition team for any hiring-related queries. To become an official supplier, send an expression of interest via mailto:talentacquisition@atturra.com.

Atturra is passionate about playing an active role in addressing the digital skills gap and being an advocate for diversity and Inclusion, and welcomes applications from all irrespective of their gender, LGBTQI identity, ethnicity, religion, physical ability, or age.

description:
Location: Sydney

Job type: Contract

If you are a talented Technical Business Analyst (Data) with a passion for turning business requirements into data-driven solutions, join our esteemed team at INGRITY. Your expertise will play a pivotal role in enabling our clients to make informed decisions and achieve their goals through innovative data strategies.

About INGRITY

INGRITY is a Microsoft Data and AI Solution Partner dedicated to delivering transformative data and AI-driven solutions. We collaborate with some of the best ASX-listed companies and medium-sized businesses, working closely with Microsoft to create measurable value for our customers. Our success is built on innovation, customer advocacy, and a strategic partnership with Microsoft.

At INGRITY:

Imagine the Impossible: It's not just an aspiration for our clients; we expect the same from our team.

INGRITY isn't your typical workplace; we thrive on the fusion of Intelligence & Grit. Prioritising personal growth, open communication, continuous learning, career progression, and accountability, we're on the lookout for individuals like you.


 * Do you seek roles fostering personal growth, allowing you to excel?
 * Do you flourish in a culture that values open communication and diverse perspectives?
 * Are you passionate about expanding your skills, eager to join a company that invests in employee development?
 * Are integrity and accountability at the core of your values?
   
   

If you answered yes to any of these questions, we invite you to explore opportunities with us and join a team committed to data smart excellence.

About The Job:

We are seeking for a Technical Business Analyst to join our team. You will have the unique opportunity to collaborate closely with our esteemed clients in these sectors and contribute to their success.

Your Responsibilities:

As Technical Business Analysts, you will be responsible for the following:


 * Translate functional requirements into technical specifications and vice versa.
 * Collaborate with business, technology, and project stakeholders to map, analyse, and translate business processes into technical and non-functional requirements.
 * Convert business requirements into technical analyses using knowledge of system capabilities, rules, and architecture best practices.
 * Collaborate with Data Architects/Modelers to deliver effective solutions.
 * Work with data producers and consumers to agree on source-to-target data mapping, utilizing Logical Data Models, Physical Data Schema designs, etc.
 * Participate in various testing phases to approve the outcomes of testing activities.
 * Ensure compliance and work with various data control standards and policies.
 * Extend your experience with SQL and Python to apply to data workflows.
 * Foster data awareness through analysis and workshops to drive innovation and facilitate better decision-making.
   
   

Your Technical Skills And Experience:


 * Minimum 5 years of solid Technical Business Analyst experience.
 * Experience in effectively conducting and completing requirements gathering collaborating with business stakeholders, delivery teams and technical experts.
 * Proficient in performing Current State vs Future State gap analysis and translating designs into fully functioning solutions.
 * Experience in developing business requirements documents and ensuring their approval and endorsement by engaging with business stakeholders.
 * Preparing deliverables including business process flow and data flow diagrams, source to target mapping, transformation rules documents, lineage, business and technical metadata, business, and data quality rules.
 * Extensive experience working with SQL across a variety of sources along with the ability to write complex SQL queries.
 * Prior experience of using programming language like Python for data insights.
 * Should possess excellent communication and stakeholder management abilities, strong problem-solving and analytical skills, keen attention to detail, and an inquisitive, open-minded approach to challenge the status quo when necessary.
 * Exposure to Data Controls specifications and documentation.
   
   

Educational Qualification: Minimum of a bachelor's degree in Computer Science, Mathematics, Statistics, or equivalent quantitative discipline.

Additional Information


 * Location: Sydney, Australia
 * Eligibility: Candidates must have full working rights in Australia to be considered for this role.
   
   

About INGRITY:

We are a fast-growing, progressive Sydney-based data & analytics company. We service many large corporates and SMBs in the financial services sector, to derive value from data. At Ingrity, we are committed to building a diverse and inclusive workforce to deliver value to customers. As a value-driven organisation, we nurture and support our people by having a laser-sharp focus on skill and talent development, collaboration, and flexibility.

description:
Company Description

At Shift, we’re business specialists dedicated to helping Australian SMEs take control of their cashflow, streamline trade terms and choose the right financial products.

We believe Australian businesses are the driving force behind our economy and the heart of our community. That’s why our business expertise, relationship focus, and market-leading technology is at the core of everything we do.

Our unique approach and collaborative culture means you can build your career with support. You’ll be joining a diverse team of over 250 people who are always looking to deliver better outcomes for the 25,000+ Australian businesses we’ve served (and counting!)

Job Description

As a Data Scientist - Classifications Model Specialist at Shift, you will play a pivotal role in maintaining and evolving our classification models. You’ll be responsible for ensuring their continued success through performance monitoring, updates, and collaboration across teams. Your work will directly impact how we leverage data to drive business decisions and optimise our systems.

What You’ll Do


 * Maintain and enhance the performance of classification models through regular updates and monitoring.
 * Support updates to model architecture, training sets, and model validation.
 * Build and implement monitoring capabilities to effectively track model health.
 * Develop and document processes to ensure smooth and consistent operations.
 * Collaborate with data science, engineering, and operational teams to align on classification needs and improvements.
   
   

Qualifications

What you’ll bring:


 * Familiarity with Python, SQL (or willingness to learn on the job), and data visualisation tools.
 * Experience with classification models or Large Language Models.
 * Strong background in data science, analytics, or a related field, with experience in maintaining or implementing machine learning models.
 * Experience in creating and managing monitoring frameworks for models or systems.
 * Proven ability to document and communicate complex processes clearly and effectively.
 * A proactive approach to problem-solving and continuous process improvement.
 * Ability to manage competing priorities and deliver high-quality results under deadlines.
 * Flexibility to adapt to evolving needs in a fast-paced environment.
 * Collaborative mindset with strong communication skills.
   
   

Additional Information

Key Benefits


 * Collaborative teams – a flat structure means everyone can learn from colleagues and senior leaders around the business.
 * Flexible working environment – we’re headquartered in North Sydney with state-based workplaces and offer a flexible work policy.
 * Family support – industry leading 26 weeks paid parental leave.
 * Varied workspaces – our office enables areas for collaboration, brainstorming and socialising as well as focus zones.
 * Wellness focus – grab a healthy breakfast, snacks and if you like keeping active, we have excellent building facilities to support you.
 * Positive environment – come together with all your colleagues at Sydney HQ every 100 days to set and collaborate on key cross functional business priorities

description:
Job description:

Job Reference: 13425 

 

Healius is an ASX-listed company providing world-class diagnostic services to consumers and doctors across Australia. Healius is supported by a team of Pathologists and Radiologists operating through a national network of 2,185 collections centres, 96 labs, and a portfolio of 18 different brands. 

 

Healius is embarking on a major strategic transformation journey to re-imagine healthcare and create customer-centric health services that leverage the latest technologies. To embark on this journey Healius is looking for highly talented individuals that are passionate about healthcare and creating a positive impact. 

 

As Data Analyst you will work with the Analytics team to discover and communicate insights into the business. This position is expected to work with a variety of stakeholders from different parts of the business to solve their analytics problems, as well as technical stakeholders to ensure data is accurate. This roles offer a package of $100 500.

 

 

Responsibilities: 

•    Undertake analysis to uncover insights from a wide range of datasets•    Development of dashboards using data visualization techniques to track key metrics for each of the businesses•    Work with internal stakeholders to understand business drivers, provide ad-hoc analysis and communicate insights & actions•    Work with analytics team to identify new data sources and specify data warehouse requirements•    Learn & apply new analytics techniques

Skills and Experience•    Tertiary qualification in engineering, mathematics, actuarial studies or a related discipline is preferable•    Strong SQL skills, able to interpret and produce complex SQL queries•    Strong Power BI skills•    Proficiency in Excel and/or Python advantageous•    Passionate about using data to deliver actionable insights•    Tech savvy, passion for learning different software•    Excellent interpersonal (verbal and written) communication skills•    Ability to manage multiple priorities, and assess and adjust quickly to changing priorities•    2-3 years’ experience in an analytics environment developing dashboards & undertaking ad-hoc analysis

 

.

 

 

Benefits, Perks and Wellbeing

As part of working for Healius, you will have access to a range of benefits & perks including:

 * Benefits platform - Reduce the impact of the cost of living with everyday savings with 500+ of Australia's most-loved brands, (from the weekly grocery shop to premium perks like holidays).
 * Fitness Passport – Access top fitness centres & pools across Australia at a subsidised rate.
 * Corporate health insurance discounts, banking benefits and novated leasing salary packaging.
 * Career growth and development opportunities with access to a comprehensive library of online courses and learning paths via our e-learning platform.
 * Confidential health and well-being support through our Employee Assistance Program, available to all employees and their family members.

 

Our Commitment to Diversity And Inclusion

Healius Pathology  is an equal opportunity employer committed to creating an inclusive workplace. We seek to recruit from diverse applicants and create teams with skills, perspectives and experiences that complement each other at work. We welcome suitably qualified applicants regardless of age, ethnicity, socio-cultural background, disability, sexual orientation or gender identity.

Healius is committed to supporting Veteran Employment - Veterans and candidates with Australian Defence Force (ADF) experience are encouraged to apply.

How To Apply

Please click the ‘Apply Now’ button to complete the pre-screening questions and submit your application.

If you would like further details please email careers@healius.com.au.See more of our jobs at www.healiuscareers.com and follow us on LinkedIn.

description:
About Us

HammondCare is a not-for-profit, values-based organisation that is passionate about improving the quality of care for people in need. As one of Australia’s most innovative health and aged care providers, we aim to set the global standard of relationship-based care for people with complex needs. HammondCare provides care primarily through hospitals, residential care homes and home-based care as well as services for dementia support, community palliative care, rehabilitation, positive aging and older persons’ mental health.

About The Role

The Business Intelligence Analyst is a critical role within the IT function. The role is to ensure HammondCare gets the best value from its investment in business systems by data collection, analysis, visualisation and quality assurance.

This is a 6 month role with the possibility of extension. The role is based at St Leonards with hybrid opportunities available.

What We Can Offer You

We care about your wellbeing at HammondCare and as a result offer a wide range of health and lifestyle benefits including:


 * NFP salary packaging ($15,900 tax free) plus meals and entertainment benefit (up to $2,650 tax free)
 * Flexible working options, including hybrid arrangements
 * Discounts on everyday products and services
 * Discounted healthcare memberships - access to network of fitness centres and pools for employees and families
 * Free access to independent counselling support for employees and families
 * Health & Wellbeing programmes
 * Reward & Recognition programmes
 * Referral bonuses
 * Career and professional development opportunities
   
   
   

Key Responsibilities Include


 * Gathering data from various sources, including databases, external data sources, and analysing it to identify trends and insights
 * Utilising data visualisation tools (PowerBI) to present data in a visually appealing and understandable manner, helping stakeholders to make informed decisions
 * Ensuring the accuracy and integrity of data by implementing data quality checks and validation processes
 * Engaging with stakeholders to gather business requirements and translating them into technical specification for data analysis
 * Creating and maintaining reports and dashboards that provide actionable insights to stakeholder
 * Staying updated with industry trends and best practices in BI and analytics and recommending improvements to existing processes and tools
 * Providing training and support to end-users on BI tools and reports, ensuring they can effectively utilize the data available to them
   
   
   

About You


 * Commitment to engage and align with HammondCare’s Mission, Motivation and Mission in Action
 * Bachelor’s degree in computer science, Information Systems, Data Analytics, or related field
 * At least 3 years demonstrated experience as an end-to-end Power BI Dataset Modelling, plus experience using premium features such as Pipeline Development
 * Power BI Desktop, Power BI Service, DAX, and Power Query essential
 * Understanding of data warehouse concepts
 * Experience with SSIS or similar ETL tools desirable
 * Exceptional stakeholder engagement at a senior level with the ability to build rapport with a diverse group of people
 * Excellent written and oral communication skills with strong presentation skills
 * Approachable, empathetic with strong relationship building skills
 * Strong analytical and problem solving skills to interpret complex data sets and derive actionable insights
   
   
   

To Apply

If you are ready to make a difference with HammondCare, Apply Now!

Pre- Employment Checks

All short-listed applicants will be asked to consent to a criminal record check and references.

HammondCare is committed to creating an inclusive workplace that promotes and values diversity and inclusion. We strive on creating an equal employment environment where everyone from any background can be themselves.
