description:
* Want to be involved in building visualizations to support an exciting, high growth business?
 * Want to join an exceptional team delivering high value solutions?
 * Want to feel like YOU really matter, and where your input is valued, and your career is as important to your employer as it is to you?




Fusion5 is in an exciting time of growth, and we are looking for a talented and highly engaged Senior Reporting Developer Analyst to join us in either Melbourne or Auckland. In return for your skills, you’ll be valued for your input and join a team like no other!




We have a very successful track record in delivering business solutions to support our fast growing enterprise. For internal reporting we use the tools that we sell and support for our customers; Fusion5 are a Microsoft Solutions Partner for Data and AI and hold the Analytics on Microsoft Azure Specialisation. We’ve been a member of the Microsoft Inner Circle since 2017 and a Cloud Solutions Partner. As part of the Inner Circle, we’re called upon to contribute to Microsoft’s own business applications strategy and the aspects that impact partners like us.




This role is an internally focused role, that will report into our cross functional Business Systems team. You will also work closely with our Microsoft Data and Analytics teams to support our reporting needs, our data lake, several major systems initiatives, and ongoing creation and maintenance of reports to support our ELT, SLT and Operational Leaders. You will love this role if you are someone who likes to take on technical challenges, thinks outside the box to deliver reporting insights, and keeps up with the latest and greatest Microsoft has to offer.




We’re looking for a strong player who can:

 * Deliver impactful solutions, translating complex business needs into clear and actionable reporting solutions that drive real value to our business.
 * Be a team player, working closely with members of multiple teams throughout the organisation to deliver cross functional data and reporting and data solutions.
 * Contribute to all aspects of our internal data lake and reporting projects including analysis and design, build, test, and deployment.
 * Become a trusted advisor to our leadership team, building strong relationships and acting as a credible source of information and guidance on all things Power BI and Microsoft Fabric.
 * Drive success, managing workloads efficiently and adhering to deadlines while maintaining high-quality standards.




The successful candidate will have the following technical capabilities:

 * Power BI expertise: In-depth knowledge of Power BI Desktop, Service, and administration, with the ability to design and implement complex data models, reports, and dashboards.
 * Data modeling: A strong understanding of dimensional modeling concepts (including Kimball) and best practices for building efficient and scalable data models in Power BI.
 * DAX proficiency: The ability to write complex DAX formulas to manipulate and analyse data, creating dynamic and insightful reports.
 * Data transformation expertise: Proficiency in Power Query (M) for data cleansing, transformation, and shaping within Power BI.
 * Data integration: Experience integrating data from various sources (relational databases, cloud storage, APIs) into Power BI using best practices for data extraction, transformation, and loading (ETL/ELT).
 * T-SQL skills: The ability to write efficient T-SQL queries to extract, manipulate and test data from relational databases for use in Power BI.
 * Microsoft Fabric and Azure familiarity: Working knowledge and experience in Microsoft Fabric and the Azure cloud platform, including Azure Synapse Analytics, Azure Data Lake Gen2, and Azure SQL Database.




The successful candidate will have the following consulting capabilities:

 * Effectively gather requirements through interviews, workshops, and user stories, ensuring a clear understanding of needs and goals.
 * Excellent documentation skills including developing functional and technical specifications, as well as assisting with the creation of accurate estimates.
 * Confidence in designing and delivering effective training sessions for end-users on Power BI and Microsoft Fabric functionalities and best practices.
 * Presents well with clear written and verbal communications. Able to communicate with a wide range of people and present information and solutions to a variety of audiences, tailoring communication style to different levels of technical expertise.
 * Strong time management and coordination skills and the ability to manage and prioritise competing tasks across multiple work streams.




It is advantageous to have the following skills:

 * Report design principles: Knowledge of data visualisation best practices and the ability to create clear, concise, and visually appealing reports and dashboards.
 * Experience with Lakehouse architecture.
 * Experience with other cloud platforms; AWS, Snowflake, Informatica
 * Experience with reporting/visualisation tools including Cognos, Tableau, Qlik
 * Experience with ELT and Modelling tools; including dbt, Coalesce, and WhereScape
 * Experience with advanced analytics using ML models.
 * Microsoft technical certifications
 * PL-300: Power BI Data Analyst Associate
 * DP-600: Fabric Analytics Engineer Associate
 * DP-203: Azure Data Engineer Associate




Our commitment to you:

 * A warm, open, and collaborative environment where you receive all the support necessary for success, including being mentored by experienced and respected Data and Analytics experts.
 * We measure our success at a team level to ensure your input forms part of the wider team and no individuals are singled out. There are no barriers to mentorship at Fusion5.
 * We are passionate about investing in the development of our team. We offer countless learning and development opportunities aligned to individuals’ development paths and encourage you to pursue industry certifications to stay ahead of the curve and reach your full potential.
 * A raft of employee benefits such as flexible working arrangements, a day off on your birthday and a day to focus on your volunteer activities each year. We have regular social occasions at all our offices and organise outings and events to suit all tastes.
 * A committed leadership team who are obsessed with your career and development. We have transformed ourselves from a traditional, performance review culture to one that focuses on Employee Development with monthly sessions that ensure we are working together on achieving your career goals.
 * An incredible team culture that must be experienced to be believed. We are a hard-working bunch that celebrates success and supports each other. Here at Fusion5, you’re never on your own with a problem. After all, a problem shared is a problem halved!




If you are interested in joining a team passionate about helping customers achieve great outcomes – get in touch.

description:
Location: Sydney

Job Type: Contract

Are you a talented Data Modeler with expertise in Snowflake and Power BI? Do you have a passion for transforming data into actionable insights? Join our esteemed team at INGRITY, where your skills as a Data Modeler will be critical in delivering value to our clients.

About INGRITY

INGRITY is a Microsoft Data and AI Solution Partner dedicated to delivering transformative data and AI-driven solutions. We collaborate with some of the best ASX-listed companies and medium-sized businesses, working closely with Microsoft to create measurable value for our customers. Our success is built on innovation, customer advocacy, and a strategic partnership with Microsoft.

About The Role:

We are looking for a talented Data Modeler to join our team immediately and contribute to an ongoing project. This role demands expertise in data modeling and analytics, creative problem-solving, excellent communication skills, and a dedication to continuous learning. You will work closely with team members and clients across various levels to deliver data assets that align with strategic goals.

Key Responsibilities:


 * Design, develop, and optimise data models for analytical and reporting purposes using Snowflake.
 * Build interactive dashboards and reports using Power BI to visualise complex datasets.
 * Provide technical subject matter expertise to support the design and implementation of a modern data platform in collaboration with Data & Analytics and broader Strategic Delivery stakeholders.
 * Create logical and physical data models to support business reporting and dashboards, using both structured and unstructured data sources.
 * Structure data optimally for reporting purposes, employing techniques like normalisation for relational models or denormalisation for data warehouses (e.g., star schema, snowflake schema).
 * Define and implement data transformation logic, preparing raw data into usable forms for reporting, including aggregations, calculations, and time-series formatting.
 * Collaborate with stakeholders to understand business requirements and translate them into scalable data solutions.
 * Ensure data integrity and compliance with data governance policies.
 * Optimise data model performance and resolve pipeline issues.
   
   

Your Technical Skills And Experience:


 * Experience: 5+ years of proven expertise in data modeling with strong proficiency in Snowflake and Power BI.
 * Data Models: Skilled in designing logical and physical data models for reporting purposes.
 * Database Design: Proficient in database design principles such as normalisation, denormalisation, star and snowflake schemas, entity-relationship modelling, and reference data management.
 * Technical Expertise: Hands-on experience with SQL and efficient database structure design. Familiarity with cloud platforms like Azure or AWS is a plus.
 * Data Warehousing: Strong understanding of data warehousing concepts, dimensional modelling, and ETL pipelines.
 * Data Solutions: Proven ability to design and implement large-scale data solutions for loading, manipulation, processing, analysis, and exploration.
 * Problem-Solving: Demonstrated initiative and problem-solving skills, with innovative approaches to data management that ensure accurate and timely outputs.
 * Master Data Management: Solid understanding of master data management principles and processes.
 * Interpersonal Skills: Strong interpersonal skills with the ability to build relationships, consult, negotiate, liaise, and influence stakeholders. Able to provide strategic advice and recommendations to internal and external teams.
   
   

How To Apply:

If you are a talented Data Modeler with expertise in Snowflake and Power BI, and you're excited about the opportunity to contribute to our data-driven success, please submit your resume, highlighting your relevant experience and achievements.

You can apply through our career site using the following link:

https://ingrity.com/careers/?jobId=jCNiUptTGrSJ

Additional Information:


 * Location: Sydney, Australia
 * Eligibility: Candidates must have full working rights in Australia to be considered for this role.
 * Shortlisted candidates will be contacted for interviews.
   
   

Join INGRITY and help us shape the future of data and AI solutions!

About INGRITY:

We are a fast-growing, progressive Sydney-based data & analytics company. We service many large corporates and SMBs in the financial services sector, to derive value from data. At Ingrity, we are committed to building a diverse and inclusive workforce to deliver value to customers. As a value-driven organisation, we nurture and support our people by having a laser-sharp focus on skill and talent development, collaboration, and flexibility.

description:
Introduction to Demyst

Demyst is a managed service that leading enterprises across the globe trust to centralize and manage all their external data needs. Demyst partners closely with clients, providing the platform and team of experts necessary to discover the right external data, onboard it compliantly and with ease, deploying it anywhere. With an industry average of 80% of data projects failing, Demyst navigates the external data minefield so our clients don't have to, enabling them to scalably manage their expansive portfolio of external data.

If you believe, like we do, that external data is the next frontier of business impact, able to power competitive advantages in industries around the world, Demyst is your new home.

The Challenge

We are looking for a strong Technical Business Analyst to join Demyst. In this role, you will be a member of a global team supporting a distributed system providing highly available, real-time data for critical industry applications around the world. You will partner with both strategic clients and Demyst stakeholders to support the full client lifecycle from pre-sales scoping, requirements gathering, data analysis and modelling, client stakeholder management, internal resource project management, testing, delivery, and support.

Your responsibilities will be to support client requirements and be the subject matter expert for the client solutions and data landscaping team.

As a Technical BA, you will lead the delivery of data solutions to our client, working directly with a team based predominantly in the APAC region supporting clients in New Zealand, Australia, Singapore, and beyond.

While Demyst is a fully-distributed company and this is a remote-first role, successful candidates are expected to be based in Australia and be able to spend significant time on-site with our Australian clients.

Responsibilities


 * Elicit requirements by interacting with stakeholders (client and internal), identify opportunities for improvement, and translate requirements into designs
 * Solve complex problems and lead process modelling
 * Conduct user needs analysis, offer advice on process improvements
 * Design and position solutions in consultation with Lead engineer to best deliver value to stakeholders
 * Identify requirements, define use cases, and understand data sources that support client data use cases
 * Provide guidance to peers, mentoring, and leading others in complex problem solving
 * Lead client testing efforts. Plan the development of client test use cases and solution execution
 * Lead triaging process of issues relating to the delivered solution raised by client and internal team
 * Organise and facilitate agile ceremonies as required by team
 * Create, maintain, and execute JIRA plans to support delivery.
 * Identify, triage and communicate risks to internal and stakeholder related to delivery.
   
   
   

Requirements


 * Degree in IT, Computer Science, Data Science, Software Engineering, or a related field
 * Experience in data science and data-centric solutions
 * Significant experience developing requirements and product specifications for new or existing applications, integrations, or solutions
 * 5 or more years of experience as a BA with a technical focus
 * Exceptional knowledge of usability, application, and operational performance considerations
 * Forward-thinking communication skills to assist with the development of documentation for software solutions
 * Impressive interpersonal skills to work with and contribute to a team environment
 * Technical background and skillset to translate requirements and project manage delivery components
 * Deep expertise in waterfall and agile deliveries
 * Product management and backlog grooming experience
 * Exceptional stakeholder management and ability to negotiate effective solutions
 * Ability to work in a remote / distributed workplace
 * Answering the screening questions: all applicants who do not provide thoughtful and detailed answers to the two questions provided in the application form will be automatically disqualified
   
   
   

Nice to Have

description:
Join the change. Together, we’ll make history.

As we keep the lights on for over four million customers and move towards a more sustainable way of life, it’s an exciting time to be at AGL. We’re re-imagining how homes and business live and work across the country and we want you to be a part of it. This moment will define our time, and your career as you work alongside Australia's best and brightest minds. You’ll grow and learn in a collaborative, safe and supportive environment and play your part in changing the course of tomorrow.

Everyone at AGL is an important part of building a better energy future and we want you to join in.

About The Role

Technology plays a critical role in the delivery of AGL’s strategy, helping our customers decarbonise the way they live, move and work and transitioning our generation portfolio.

Our Cloud Analytics and Data Platforms Technology team is currently on a mission to transform our data governance capabilities across AGL. We have an exciting new opportunity for a data governance champion to join us and help us on this transformative journey.

If you're passionate about fostering a culture of data stewardship and ready to lead the effort in building and strengthening our data governance framework, this is your opportunity to make an impact. We're looking for an analyst who has a strong understanding of data management principles, delivering data governance initiatives and providing training and guidance on best practices.?

What You’ll Be Doing


 * Develop and implement a comprehensive onboarding program for new data stewards
 * Design and deliver training sessions on data governance policies, best practices, and tools for data stewards and other stakeholders
 * Serve as a point of contact for data stewards, addressing questions and providing guidance on data governance processes and tools
 * Monitor the performance and effectiveness of data stewardship activities, providing feedback and coaching as needed
 * Facilitate regular check-ins and workshops to discuss challenges, share successes, and promote collaboration among data stewards
 * Ensure that data management practices comply with relevant regulations and standards, monitor and assess data quality metrics, identify data quality issues, and work with data owners to resolve them
 * Prepare and present reports on data governance activities, data quality, and compliance status.
   
   
   

About You

What you’ll bring:


 * Background in information management, business intelligence or related discipline
 * Strong understanding of data governance principles, frameworks, and best practices
 * Strong understanding of data modelling, data mapping and data structures.?
 * Familiarity with data governance tools such as Purview, Collibra, Informatica, or similar platforms and frameworks, such as DAMA-DMBOK.?
 * Strong understanding of data architecture principles, data management practices, data quality best practices and industry standards.?
 * Excellent analytical and problem-solving skills?
 * Effective communication and interpersonal skills, with the ability to collaborate with cross-functional teams.?
   
   
   

What We Offer


 * Flexible working options including hybrid work.
 * Discounts on energy, telcos and solar plans.
 * Participate in Energise - our reward & recognition program.
 * Access 20 weeks of paid parental leave for the primary caregiver.
 * Access to an additional week of recharge leave per year.
 * Play an active role in our diversity & inclusion initiatives.
 * Novated leasing and Electric Vehicle subscriptions.
 * Access to study assistance, AGL's share purchase plan and insurance deals.
 * Benefits may change over time and vary based on role type and location.
   
   
   

Join us at AGL Energy and be a part of shaping tomorrow

Inclusion at AGL

At AGL, we value diversity and welcome applicants from various backgrounds, including Aboriginal and/or Torres Strait Islander peoples, individuals with disabilities, culturally diverse individuals, and members of the LGBTQ+ community. AGL is dedicated to maintaining a diverse workforce and encourages applicants to share their lived experiences.

We offer reasonable adjustments throughout the recruitment process and respect the privacy of those who choose not to disclose. To learn more visit: www.agl.com.au/careers

AGL is a Circle Back Initiative employer - we commit to respond to every applicant.

Our pre-employment screening process includes a Nationally Coordinated Criminal History Check and a medical assessment if necessary.

The information provided as part of your application to AGL will be managed in accordance with the AGL Privacy Policy.

AGL does not accept agency submissions unless approval has been granted by a member of the Talent Acquisition team. Candidates submitted by an agency without approval will not be considered by AGL.

We are looking for a highly skilled and proactive Data Engineer to join our team and support the Data Quality Uplift Project. This critical role will involve prototyping data quality rules, identifying and addressing ad-hoc data quality issues in collaboration with business analysts and system specialists, and developing rules and workflows within a dedicated data quality platform to be selected in early 2025.

 * Strong analytical and problem-solving skills, with the ability to collaborate effectively in a cross-functional team environment.

description:
Brief Description

About The Company

Compare the Market – yes, the one with the meerkats – is a high-growth FinTech company on a transformational journey. We are focused on designing, building, and delivering the very best home loan, energy, insurance, and health comparison experience in Australia. Okay, in the world!

We are all about Customer first, teamwork, making a difference, and treating the business as our own – without compromise. These values are critical to delivering on our purpose: “to make a difference in the lives of Australians by simplifying the process of making sound financial decisions”.

About The Role:

Are you ready to elevate your career? Compare the Market is looking for a Senior Data Engineer to join our innovative team. As we continue to advance our modern data platform on AWS and Databricks, this role offers the opportunity to shape the data foundations and provide technical leadership within the engineering team and across broader business stakeholders. Reporting to the Lead Data Engineer, you'll contribute to developing scalable data solutions that drive actionable insights, supporting our customers and overall business growth.

As the Senior Data Engineer, you will be a hands-on expert, actively guiding architecture and solution design while contributing to the wider data strategy. You'll mentor the engineering team in designing and developing the data platform and ecosystem. Collaborating with data scientists, business intelligence developers, data architects, and other IT and business teams, you'll play a crucial role in driving innovation and excellence across data science, business intelligence, and machine learning initiatives.

What You’ll Do:


 * Collaborate with business and IT teams to define business problems, refine requirements, and design and develop data solutions.
 * Ensure data engineering solutions align with data architecture and component designs.
 * Lead the development and implementation of the data engineering roadmap.
 * Manage data pipelines from acquisition to integration and consumption, architecting, building, and maintaining them for specific use cases.
 * Promote best practices in data management, including Data Lakes, Data Warehouses, Data Quality, Lineage, and DataOps.
 * Work closely with Data Architects, DevOps, and Data Engineers to design integrated data applications.
 * Drive automation by using innovative tools and techniques to streamline data preparation and integration tasks, minimising manual efforts, and improving productivity.
 * Identify, design, and implement scalable solutions that allow for future reuse.
 * Develop production-ready data applications and pipelines within a cloud environment.
 * Conduct root cause analysis on internal and external data and processes to address business questions and identify opportunities for improvement.
   
   
   

What You’ll Bring:


 * Tertiary Qualifications in Computer Science, IT, or a relevant discipline
 * Demonstrated extensive experience in a similar role
 * Strong experience with cloud EDWs (AWS/GCP), Data Lakes, and Information Governance Suites (Lineage, Glossary, Reference Data).
 * Skilled in data models (e.g., Star Schema, Data Vault) and developing unified data layers or presentation layers.
 * Proven experience with modern platforms like Databricks or Snowflake, and expertise in Python/PySpark for stream and batch solutions.
 * Proficient in SQL, with a solid command of the language.
 * Experience with traditional on-premise EDW/ETL environments (e.g., IBM Infosphere DataStage, Microsoft SQL Server) is a plus.
 * Highly regarded experience in building metadata-driven, automated solutions.
 * Skilled in optimising processes on both legacy systems and cloud platforms.
 * Git experience for source code management is desirable.
 * Familiar with DevOps practices and CI/CD tools for efficient data solution deployment.
 * Strong understanding of the Data & Insights lifecycle.
 * Agile experience using tools like Jira and Confluence.
   
   
   

Our Benefits

At Compare the Market, we offer a dynamic and collaborative work environment where your talents will be recognised and rewarded. You’ll have the opportunity to make a meaningful impact and contribute to our continued success. As well as ample opportunities for growth and development, we also provide:


 * Vibrant and social community who have annual celebrations, family fun days and regular events.
 * Enjoy flexible work arrangements, including the option of one day working from home each week or a 9-day fortnight.
 * Enjoy additional leave days - ‘ME’ leave and ‘Volunteer Day’ leave.
 * Study support (up to 50% of tuition fees for relevant courses) and professional membership reimbursement.
 * Employee discounts on Car, Home, Travel insurance.
 * Income protection insurance provided to support you in the event of non-work-related illness or injury.
 * Discounts with a broad range of providers, including gym memberships, accommodation, dental care and more.
   
   
   

Compare the Market is an Equal Opportunity Employer, and we encourage all applicants to apply. We acknowledge that we are strengthened by diversity.

Want to know more? Then apply now! It’s Simples!

Please note that this role is only available to candidates with unlimited Australian working rights, as sponsorship is not available.


 * Note to Recruiters: We politely ask that you avoid making any approaches or sending any unsolicited resumes to our Recruitment Team or Hiring Leaders across our business.
title: Senior Data Engineer

description:
Job Description

Join the team redefining how the world experiences design.

Hey, g'day, mabuhay, kia ora, ??, hallo, vítejte!

Thanks for stopping by. We know job hunting can be a little time consuming and you're probably keen to find out what's on offer, so we'll get straight to the point.

Where And How You Can Work

Our flagship campus is in Sydney. We also have a campus in Melbourne and co-working spaces in Brisbane, Perth and Adelaide. But you have choice in where and how you work. That means if you want to do your thing in the office (if you're near one), at home or a bit of both, it's up to you.

What You’d Be Doing In This Role

As Canva scales change continues to be part of our DNA. But we like to think that's all part of the fun. So this will give you the flavour of the type of things you'll be working on when you start, but this will likely evolve.

At The Moment, This Role Is Focused On


 * Build systems to generate and edit designs – working closely with other ML engineers, backend engineers, frontend engineers, designers, and product managers to deliver cutting-edge design generation systems and techniques that empower users.
 * Hypothesis-driven development of data and ML-driven features across Canva.
 * Engineering implementation: developing and implementing ML models and features, as well as using third party APIs and pre-trained models when appropriate.
 * Running offline and online experiments.
 * Investigating and spiking applications of data and ML across the Canva product, considering tradeoffs between different approaches and rapidly shipping.
 * Contributing to the full life cycle of ML/data models: data analysis, data preprocessing and pipeline, modelling, tuning and productization.
 * Improving the scalability, speed and performance of existing models.
 * Working alongside data specialists, software engineers and product owners to identify business and growth opportunities.
 * Designing and creating new data workflows and deploying these workflows to users.
 * Sharing and articulating statistical analysis, modelling, experiment and results to technical and non-technical audiences.
   
   
   

You're probably a match if


 * You have great research skills with the ability to stay abreast of the latest developments in deep learning and generative AI.
 * You are capable to translate cutting-edge research into practical solutions that enhance design generation product.
 * You have experience or strong interest in design. This team works at the intersection of engineering and design so a genuine desire or proven experience in this space is essential.
 * You have strong coding proficiency in Python, interviews will be in Python.
 * You are familiar with several of the following: TensorFlow, PyTorch, scikit-learn, Kubernetes, Solr/ElasticSearch, dataset creation.
 * You have strong understanding of Computer Science/Engineering fundamentals and first principles covering system design, data structures, architecture, and design patterns.
 * SQL experience preferred.
   
   
   

About The Team

The Generative Experience Group’s mission is to “Empower the world to design by developing and applying AI that can create every type of design and ingredient on Canva.”

This is an exciting and emerging problem space with weekly innovations. Our close-knit team collaborates with engineers to prototype and develop new experiences, works with researchers to explore uncharted territories, and tackles some of today's biggest challenges. We continuously improve our current offerings to create better ways for people to achieve their design dreams. Our goal is to create magical, emotionally engaging AI experiences that charm, simplify complex tasks, and foster meaningful connections.

What's in it for you?

Achieving our crazy big goals motivates us to work hard - and we do - but you'll experience lots of moments of magic, connectivity and fun woven throughout life at Canva, too. We also offer a range of benefits to set you up for every success in and outside of work.

Here's a Taste Of What's On Offer


 * Equity packages - we want our success to be yours too
 * Inclusive parental leave policy that supports all parents & carers
 * An annual Vibe & Thrive allowance to support your wellbeing, social connection, office setup & more
 * Flexible leave options that empower you to be a force for good, take time to recharge and supports you personally
   
   
   

Check out lifeatcanva.com for more info.

Other Stuff To Know

We make hiring decisions based on your experience, skills and passion, as well as how you can enhance Canva and our culture. When you apply, please tell us the pronouns you use and any reasonable adjustments you may need during the interview process.

We celebrate all types of skills and backgrounds at Canva so even if you don’t feel like your skills quite match what’s listed above - we still want to hear from you!

Please note that interviews are conducted virtually.

description:

title: Machine Learning Engineer - Support

description:
At Oracle Health and AI (OHAI), we're not just building the future of healthcare applications—we're redefining it. Our diverse team of visionaries and innovators is at the forefront of cutting-edge AI technology, particularly Generative AI, where creativity meets precision. As pioneers in this space, we've consistently delivered industry-leading AI solutions, notably for the Oracle Clinical Digital Assistant, solidifying our reputation as trusted leaders in the field.




Now, as we expand rapidly, we're channelling our expertise into transformative Generative AI solutions that promise to revolutionize healthcare for millions. Operating within a dynamic, agile environment, we enjoy strong backing from senior leadership and have a clear, impactful mission. Our close partnership with Oracle Cerner enables us to directly influence patient care on a massive scale, driving real change.




As our Senior AI/ ML Engineer or Principal AI/ ML Engineer, you'll be at the heart of this transformation, shaping the future of AI at OHAI. Your expertise in building applications leveraging Large Language Models (LLMs) and Generative AI will be crucial in bringing our visionary solutions to life, delivering groundbreaking healthcare applications that will set new standards across the industry.




Responsibilities:

 * Partner with product managers to transform business and product visions into groundbreaking AI projects that push the boundaries of what’s possible in healthcare.
 * Collaborate with internal teams or external vendors to collect and curate high-quality data for training and testing AI models.
 * Rapidly develop AI-based prototypes and demos to showcase solutions and ideas to stakeholders, incorporating their feedback into future development iterations.
 * Define and implement sophisticated evaluation metrics to measure and analyze model performance.
 * Run experiments and optimize models through hyperparameter tuning to achieve peak performance.
 * Conduct quantitative and qualitative analysis, including error analysis and ablation studies, to enhance model development and data quality.
 * Prepare detailed reports with evidence-based insights to support strategic decision-making.
 * Work closely with team members to ensure successful and timely model delivery and service integration.
 * Develop innovative healthcare and enterprise services by leveraging the latest advancements in generative AI, machine learning, and deep learning.
 * Participate actively in project planning, review, and retrospective sessions.
 * Write production-grade code, advocate for best coding practices, and conduct peer reviews to maintain high engineering standards.
 * Identify potential risks at the critical intersection of business and engineering, and take proactive measures to ensure our plans and executions stay on track.







Qualifications and Experience:

 * Proven experience designing and deploying scalable AI models for production environments, with a successful track record of applying AI in real-world applications. Experience building applications using Large Language Models (LLMs) is a strong advantage.
 * Demonstrated hands-on experience in full-stack development of generative AI models, from data preparation to model deployment, ensuring end-to-end AI system functionality.
 * Practical experience with emerging LLM frameworks and plugins such as LangChain, LlamaIndex, VectorStores, Retrievers, LLM Cache, LLMOps (MLFlow), LMQL, and Guidance, showcasing your ability to stay at the forefront of AI technology.
 * Proven experience in designing data collection and annotation solutions, as well as systematic evaluation processes crucial for developing and maintaining high-quality production systems.

Education:

description:
We are Rokt, a hyper-growth ecommerce leader. We enable companies to unlock value by making each transaction relevant at the moment that matters most, when customers are buying. Together, Rokt's AI-based relevance Platform and scaled ecommerce Network powers billions of transactions. In December 2022, Rokt's valuation increased to $2.4 billion USD, allowing us to expand rapidly across 15 countries.

The Rokt engineering team builds best-in-class ecommerce technology that provides personalized and relevant experiences for customers globally and empowers marketers with sophisticated, AI-driven tooling to better understand consumers. Our bespoke platform handles millions of transactions per day and considers billions of data points which give engineers the opportunity to build technology at scale, collaborate across teams and gain exposure to a wide range of technology.

At Rokt, we practice transparency in career paths and compensation.

At Rokt, we believe in transparency, which is why we have a well-defined career ladder with transparent compensation and clear career paths based on competency and ability. Rokt'stars constantly strive to raise the bar, pushing the envelope of what is possible.

We are looking for a Senior Machine Learning Engineer

Compensation: $190,000-$235,000 including superannuation, plus employee equity plan grant & world class benefits.

As a Senior Machine Learning Engineer, you are someone who has significant expertise in both machine learning and software engineering. You will be working with our engineering and product teams to design, build and productionise proprietary machine learning models to solve different business challenges including smart bidding, lookalike modelling, forecasting, etc.

About The Role


 * Collaborate closely with product managers and other engineers to understand business priorities, frame machine learning problems, and architect machine learning solutions.
 * Build and productionise machine learning models including data preparation/processing pipelines, machine learning orchestrations, improvements of services performance and reliability and etc.
 * Contribute and maintain the high quality of the code base with tests that provide a high level of functional coverage as well as non-functional aspects with load testing, unit testing, integration testing, etc.
 * Keep track of emerging tech and trends, research the state-of-art deep learning models, prototype new modelling ideas, and conduct offline and online experiments.
 * Share your knowledge by giving brown bags, tech talks, and evangelising appropriate tech and engineering best practices.
   
   

Requirements

About You:


 * PhD in Machine Learning
 * Extensive knowledge in and experience with some of the following areas - Bayesian methods, Recommender systems, multi-task modelling, meta-learning, click through rate modelling or conversion rate modelling.
 * 3+ years of industry experience in building production-grade machine learning systems with all aspects of model training, tuning, deploying, serving and monitoring.
 * Experience with Kubeflow (or similar), Tensorflow and Feature Store in a production environment is a massive plus.
 * Bonus points if you are familiar with any of the following architectures or have experience with the models mentioned in this benchmark: DCNV2, MMOE, Deep & Wide, ESMM, xDeepFM, and GDCN.
   
   

Benefits

About Rokt'stars:

As a mission-driven, hyper-growth community of curious explorers, our ambition is to unlock the full potential in ecommerce and beyond. Our bias for action means we are not afraid to quickly venture into uncharted territories, take risks or challenge the status quo; in doing so we either win or learn. We work together as one aligned team never letting egos get in the way of brilliant ideas. We value diversity, transparency and smart humble people who enjoy building a disruptive business together. We pride ourselves on being a force for good as we make the world better.

About The Benefits

We leverage best-in-class technology and market-leading innovation in AI and ML, with all of that being underlined by building and maintaining a fantastic and inclusive culture where people can be their authentic selves, and offering a great list of perks and benefits to go with it:


 * Accelerate your career. We offer roadmaps to leadership and an annual $5000 training allowance
 * Become a shareholder. Every Rokt'star gets equity in the company
 * Enjoy catered lunch every day and healthy snacks in the office. Plus join the gym on us!
 * Extra leave (bonus annual leave, sabbatical leave etc.)
 * Work with the greatest talent in town
 * See the world! We have offices in New York, Seattle, Sydney, Tokyo and London
   
   

We believe we're better together. We love spending time together and are in the office most days (teams are in the office 4 days per week). We also get that you need to balance your life and your commitments so you have the flexibility to manage your own hours and can spend up to a week of every quarter working from anywhere.

If this sounds like a role you'd enjoy, apply here and you'll hear from our recruiting team.

GMW is Australia’s largest rural water corporation, managing 70 per cent of Victoria’s stored water resources and Australia’s largest irrigation delivery network. We provide services to 25,000 customers, supporting a diverse, productive and sustainable region.

Join a dynamic and innovative team where your expertise in data analysis, Power BI reporting, and data governance skills will play a key role in delivering impactful data solutions. As a Data Governance and Reporting Analyst, you’ll leverage your technical skills to create high-quality reports, dashboards, and data insights that drive informed decision-making across the organisation.

Ensure the integrity, availability, and security of GMW’s data, helping to establish and maintain robust data governance practices across the organisation.

Develop and enforce data quality standards and processes, conduct data quality assessments, and provide guidance to business units on best practices.

Collaborate: Work with cross-functional teams to develop data-driven solutions.

Qualifications:

Advanced use of Microsoft platforms, specifically Power BI, Azure and Excel.

A relevant qualification in business or information technology is desirable.

Relevant work experience in a Data Governance / Data analysis role. Please note that graduates are encouraged to apply




Essential Attributes:

Proficiency in Microsoft applications, including Power BI and Excel.

Ability to analyse and validate the business data needs of stakeholders.

Capability to answer technical data-related queries for different audiences.

Excellent customer service and communication skills.

Strong documentation skills.

Exceptional ability to prioritize tasks and self-manage workload.

Commitment to continuous improvement of data, systems, and processes.




Benefits

A competitive salary - classification C Band in line with Goulburn-Murray Water 2021 Enterprise Agreement

A workplace where our values are genuinely demonstrated and celebrated

The flexibility to work between home and the office and adjust days and times as needed

Individually tailored learning and development opportunities

The opportunity to make your mark in the water industry and regional Victoria

Part of a larger team in a multi-disciplinary environment, with a great culture and undergoing an exciting time of progress

Great time to make the move to regional Victoria for a different lifestyle, career opportunities and challenge.




For more information or to view the position description please visit our website. For a confidential conversation, please contact Manager Information & Insights, John Weber on 0400 005 039.




Applications close on Tuesday 10 December 2024. To apply for this role please complete the GMW application form provided on our careers page and email together with a copy of your current CV to recruitment@gmwater.com.au.




GMW is an equal opportunity employer supporting diversity and inclusion in the workplace. GMW encourages people with diverse backgrounds, experience and perspectives to apply.




We welcome applications from people with disability and aim to provide an inclusive and accessible workplace. If you need any help with the application process or would like to discuss reasonable adjustments to support you to take part in an interview, please contact: recruitment@gmwater.com.au

description:
Help us deliver like never before? 

We’re looking for a Senior Data Scientist to join our diverse, talented and innovative digital technology team who together are helping our customers and communities build a better future. Together, we design, build and maintain products, services and experiences that Australian's love and trust, while delivering a sustainable future for Australia Post, and you could be part of that.? 

 

We're empowered to deliver for our teams and to delight our customers. We provide an inclusive and supportive environment that nurtures talented people, trusts our teams to deliver their best, and leverages modern work practices and technologies. It's an unexpectedly dynamic and collaborative culture that feels more like a start-up than a 213-year old icon.? 

Whilst this is a senior position we are open to someone who is a strong cultural fit with a proactive approach to learning irrespective of experience! 

What you’ll deliver with us?

As our Senior Data Scientist you will contribute to the development of a thriving AI/ML craft at Post and support colleagues to the field to unlock business value using critical thinking, analytics and AI/ML. Reporting directly into the Data Science Manager, the Senior Data Scientist will collaborate with technical and business stakeholders to transform complex problems into analytical, ML and AI solutions. This role operated across initiatives including digital self-service, digital network map, forecasting and AI/ML democratisation to name a few! You will be walking into an established team, our Senior Data Scientists collaborate closely with technical and business peers to trial new approaches and productionise enterprise solutions that meet Australia Post's strategic goals of: support our people, delight our customers and communities and create a sustainable future. We have an ambition AI transformation agenda and as such is important to have experience in Agile or Kanban delivery methodologies or IT service delivery.

You’ll also be

 * Providing development, thought and project leadership in one or more of the following domains: Natural Language Processing (NLP), optimisation of network operations, generative or agentic AI testing, forecasting, price forecasting.
 * Lead the end-to-end development and delivery of analytics/AI solutions and support business adoption/ operationalisation.
 * Design, build, train, evaluate, deploy and monitor advanced machine learning models from POC to production-grade (enterprise-scale).
 * Building and enabling colleagues & broader business capability in data science/AI/ML and supporting the achievement of Australia Post's vision for AI.  ?
 * Lead the translation of business problems into requirements that can be solved via analytics/AI.
 * Comfortable working with large data sets in a hyperscale environment (GCP preferred) 

About you? 

We are seeking a strong team player who can develop productive relationships with both technical and non-technical peers, breaking down barriers and influencing outcomes. You will be working with a highly skilled ML Engineering team as well as the broader Data & AI services team including Platforms, Solutions, Governance partnerships and Transformation. Outside of Enterprise Services you will collaboration with Network Operations, Retail, Customer Service, Sales, Finance, and other business teams. Ultimately, we are looking for someone who is highly enthusiastic about AI and is committed to developing in this area. This is an inclusive team where team members are encouraged to be open about knowledge gaps, which fosters a team culture of collaboration and upskilling.

You’ll also need?  

 * Experience with delivering data analytics outcomes that lead to actionable outcomes.  Prefer experience in an industry role with business facing work.
 * Strong background in analytics with experience utilising data science approaches and forecasting.
 * Experience utilising a variety analytic/AI/ML approaches with and understanding of end-to-end data analytics processes (e.g. CRISP-DM)
 * Proficient in SQL, Python and MLOps platforms (Vertex preferred), including code management tools.
 * Good understanding of AI/ML trends and technological advancements, especially as they relate to enterprise use.
 * Critical thinker and strong communicator; able to evaluate and convey technical choices.
 * Commercial understanding of operations focused industry e.g. utilities, eCommerce, logistics etc. where data is a key differentiator or value provider.
 * A background or degree in a relevant discipline including engineering, science, econometrics, maths, statistics, computer science, data science etc.  

If you do not meet all of these requirements, please still apply! We are open to a wide range of skills.

How we’ll deliver for you? 

 * Join one of the most culturally and linguistically diverse workforces in Australia, where we’re all ages, genders and come from all walks of life.
 * Immerse yourself in the AP Way – where every single team member partakes in a learning module to help understand the vital role we play in delivering on our strategy and purpose
 * We offer great development opportunities in a growing Enterprise Service function. 

We’re delivering together 

At Australia Post, we acknowledge the Traditional?Custodians of the land on which we operate, live and gather as employees. 

We believe our business should reflect the diverse communities we operate in and are proud to be an inclusive workplace for people from all walks of life. We encourage applications?from people of all ages, genders and backgrounds including Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples, People with Disability, LGBTQIA+ and Refugees. We are one of the largest organisations in Australia to successfully achieve Disability Confident Recruiter status. We are committed to providing an inclusive and barrier-free recruitment process and workplace for those living with a disability and are committed to reviewing and removing bias in our processes to create a gender-equitable recruitment experience and workplace.  If you have any questions about accessibility, please contact our Diversity & Inclusion team on inclusivecareers@auspost.com.au

description:
Melanoma Institute Australia (MIA) is an independent, non-profit organisation with its head office located near North Sydney. MIA is affiliated with the University of Sydney and is world’s largest treatment and research centre with a single focus on melanoma, and our mission is to reach zero deaths from melanoma this decade.

The Personalised Immunotherapy Program (PIP) is a 5-year program which applies machine learning- based models to identify patients with cancer that is likely to be unresponsive to anti-cancer immunotherapies. PIP aims to ensure each patient’s cancer is screened for genetic, transcriptomic, and immune profiles to identify patients unlikely to benefit from standard therapies. The team has a wealth of multi-omics datasets and is currently deploying predictive models into oncology clinicals in real-time.

The PIP team is seeking a full time experienced Computational Data Scientist with a strong analytical background to leverage the vast resources available to monitor and improve the accuracy of melanoma diagnosis, prognosis, and suitability of anti-cancer therapies. The position entails deploying machine learning models to identify patient responses to therapies using clinical and multi-omics data sets and overseeing the long-term accuracy of the predictive models. The candidate will also build on these models with new approaches and additional information from novel technologies to improve patient selection for systemic therapies.

The data scientist will be responsible for the implementation of predictive models into a biomarker program within oncology clinics. The role will work alongside multiple clinical and research teams to interrogate multi-omics datasets, imaging data and other resources available at MIA. This role will require the candidate to have excellent computational skills, preferred experience in the cancer setting, and a passion to improve cancer patient outcomes.

The successful candidate will be part of the PIP team that resides within the Translational Research Laboratory of the Melanoma Institute Australia, based at The University of Sydney Camperdown campus. This is a fixed term position until December 2026 with view to a permanent role upon completion of fixed term contract. Applications that do not address the selection criteria will not be processed.

Key Selection Criteria

To Be Successful In This Role You Will Have


 * PhD in data science, computational biology or related field
 * Demonstrated skills in computer languages (eg –Python, R)
 * Experience in processing and analysing multi-omics and/or imaging datasets.
 * Experience in deploying machine learning models
 * Scientific track record in developing machine learning models
 * Experience in the clinical integration of multi-omics datasets
 * Knowledge in deploying predictive models in the clinical setting
 * Excellent project management skills with the ability to multitask.
 * Preferred working knowledge of cancer biology and/or immunology
 * Preferred interest in spatial biology and emerging technologies.
   
   

If you have the right experience for this role, please submit a covering letter along with your resume, addressing your experience in relation to the key responsibilities.

Applicants must have full working rights in Australia. Only shortlisted candidates will be contacted. Please no recruitment agencies.

Please apply by clicking on the appropriate link on this job board. The role may be open until 24 December, interview will commence after the holiday break unless an exceptional candidate is identified beforehand.

We pay our respects to the Traditional Custodians of the lands on which Melanoma Institute Australia works, and their Elders both past and present, and acknowledge the deep, continuing connection of Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples to the land, waters, and sky.

Our Energy Management Department is looking for a Senior Energy Markets Analyst to join its Markets team.

The Energy Management team mission is to optimize operating assets in the energy markets and to support Neoen’s expansion plans. The team is defined by a combination of market expertise, advanced quantitative capabilities and software development skills.

The Senior Energy Markets Analyst will have the following responsibilities:


 * Monitor, analyse and report market activity and market performances of our operating assets in the NEM and the WEM
 * Identify strategies to improve market performances, and work alongside our Optimisation Engineers, Software Developers and Control Center Operators to implement them
 * Analyse and report Neoen’s portfolio merchant exposure, identify and execute hedging opportunities using structured products (baseload, fixed solar shapes…)
 * Contribute to the team’s efforts to industrialize our market analysis practices, developing and implementing new tools to automatize market monitoring and reporting tasks
 * Assess market fundamentals and trends, and evaluate impacts for Neoen’s portfolio of assets (wind and solar cannibalization, negative prices…)
 * Deliver long-term power markets analysis, leveraging scenarios and data procured from external experts and developing internal models
 * Support Neoen Australia development teams in projecting future revenues of new wind, solar and BESS assets, improving our internal revenue models
 * Combine quantitative results and market knowledge into business and strategic recommendations
 * Participate in PPA negotiations and valuation
 * Contribute to the development of innovative business models (Baseload PPAs, Virtual Battery…)
   
   

The candidate will need the following skills and experience to succeed in this role:


 * Master’s degree in Engineering, Applied Mathematics, Data or Computer Science
 * 3+ year of experience in a market analyst role in the NEM
 * Proficiency in Python and knowledge of SQL
 * Experience in version management tool (Git)
 * Knowledge in constrained optimization models (LP, MILP) would be a plus
 * Fluent in English
 * On the soft skills side, we are looking for someone:
 * proactive and curious with a strong appetite for proposing and exploring new ideas
 * Interpersonal skills and ability to work in a transversal organization
 * Rigorous, organized and ready to work on several projects in parallel in a fast running and high skilled environment
 * Strong communication skills
   
   

The position can be based in Canberra, Sydney or Brisbane.

description:
About The Role

The Senior Quantitative Analyst plays a crucial role in the Bank Treasury Department by utilising advanced quantitative techniques to support decision-making processes related to risk management, asset-liability management, liquidity management, and financial modelling. This position is responsible for developing sophisticated quantitative models, analysing financial data, and providing insights that contribute to the overall financial health and strategic objectives of the bank.

This role will develop and maintain quantitative models to assess and manage various financial risks, including interest rate risk, market risk, credit risk, and liquidity risk. These models will utilize techniques such as stochastic modelling, Monte Carlo simulations, behavioural analysis, and stress testing methodologies.

In addition, the role involves analyzing financial data, market trends, and macroeconomic factors to identify opportunities and risks within the bank's portfolio, providing actionable insights to senior management for strategic decision-making. The candidate will also assist in the development and implementation of Asset-Liability Management (ALM) strategies to optimize the bank's balance sheet, ensuring alignment with regulatory requirements and internal risk appetite. Furthermore, thorough validation and testing of quantitative models will be conducted to ensure accuracy, reliability, and compliance with regulatory standards such as APRA Prudential Standards.

About You


 * Postgraduate qualifications in quantitative finance, mathematics, statistics, economics, IT, or a related field.
 * Senior level experience in quantitative analysis within the banking or financial services industry, with a focus on treasury management, risk management, or asset-liability management.
 * Strong proficiency in programming languages such as Python, R, or MATLAB, SAS, SQL, VBA and Advanced Excel modelling for quantitative analysis and modelling.
 * Deep understanding of financial instruments, derivatives, and their pricing models.
 * Experience with quantitative modelling techniques, including time series analysis, regression analysis, and machine learning algorithms.
 * Solid knowledge of banking regulations and regulatory requirements related to risk management (e.g. APRA Prudential Standards).

Research Associate in Data Science and AI, UNSW Canberra

Employment type: Fixed-term, full-time

Duration: Up to 24 months

Remuneration: Level A, Step 6 $110,059 plus 17% super

Location: UNSW Canberra, ADFA Campus

About UNSW Canberra

University of New South Wales (UNSW) in Canberra has multiple locations in the Nation’s Capital.

UNSW Canberra distinguishes itself from other institutions by its commitment to being thoughtful, practical, and purposeful in all endeavours. This combined approach is integral to the university's impact and contributes to its recognition as one of the top 20 universities globally, as well as a proud member of Australia's esteemed Group of Eight. Choosing a career at UNSW means embracing an environment where thriving, facing challenges, and engaging in meaningful work are not just encouraged but integral to the university experience. If you seek a career where you can excel and contribute meaningfully, you've found the right place.

At UNSW, we pride ourselves on being a workplace where the best people come to do their best work.

Why Your Role Matters

Defence Trailblazer Program is an exciting partnership with industry and is strengthening Australia’s defence capabilities and assets. The position will involve research activity in multidisciplinary settings requiring knowledge and skills in conducting aviation research, focusing on the use of Uncrewed Aerial Systems (UAS) and Artificial Intelligence (AI). The Research Associate will contribute to conducting research activities, provide summary of results, and undertake a range of research administrative duties.

Who You Are (skills And Experience)


 * A PhD in Data Science, Artificial Intelligence/ Machine Learning
 * Application of previous research in the fields of Aviation, Human Factors, or related discipline, and/or relevant work experience is preferred
 * Proven commitment to proactively keeping up to date with discipline knowledge and developments.
 * Demonstrated ability to undertake high quality academic research and conduct independent research with limited supervision.
 * Demonstrated track record of publications and conference presentations relative to opportunity.
 * Demonstrated ability to work in a team, collaborate across disciplines and build effective relationships.
 * Demonstrated ability to communicate and interact with a diverse range of stakeholders and students
   
   
   

Benefits And Culture

UNSW is committed to helping staff balance work-life responsibilities, by providing access to high-quality services, facilities, and flexible work and leave arrangements.


 * Generous superannuation contributions
 * Employee discounts
 * Flexible 17% superannuation contributions, additional leave-loading payments and salary sacrifice
 * Additional three days leave during December festive period
 * A commitment to lifelong learning
 * UNSW-wide strategy to focus on Healthy Body, Healthy Mind, Healthy Places and Healthy Culture.
   
   
   

Eligibility

The successful candidate will be required to undertake pre-employment checks prior to commencement in this role. The checks that will be undertaken are listed in the Position Description. You will not be required to provide any further documentation or information regarding the checks until directly requested by UNSW.

To be successful you will hold Australian Working Rights. UNSW is unable to offer visa sponsorship for this position.

The University reserves the right not to proceed with any appointment.

How To Apply

Make each day matter with a meaningful career at UNSW. Please apply via our online recruitment system.

In Your Application, Please Include


 * your CV
 * a 2-page cover letter addressing the skills and experience outlined in the Position Description.

description:
Overview

Working at Atlassian

Atlassians can choose where they work – whether in an office, from home, or a combination of the two. That way, Atlassians have more control over supporting their family, personal goals, and other priorities. We can hire people in any country where we have a legal entity. Interviews and onboarding are conducted virtually, a part of being a distributed-first company.

Responsibilities

Responsibilities

Atlassian is hiring a principal data scientist to join our People Insights team, a group of analysts, data scientists, behavioral scientists, researchers and business partners, who use data and research to inform strategic and operational issues facing our leaders, teams, and people. You will collaborate with business and people leaders across Atlassian to understand the people insights needed to make decisions, and collaborating with others on the People Insights team to deliver. You will report to the Head of People Insights.

In This Role, You Will


 * Deeply understand the needs of our business stakeholders, translate those needs into analytical and research projects, and deliver science-backed insights and recommendations to drive action
 * Collaborate with behavioral scientists, data scientists and others to deliver insights in a way that is scalable, meets stakeholder needs and is actionable.
 * Act as a subject matter expert to business leaders on high priority projects tied to company objectives.
 * Take complex analyses and insights and present them in a way that is clear and relevant to your stakeholders with behavioral scientists, business partners and others to understand the people insights needed to drive decision-making at Atlassian, and design products and insights in a way that motivates and inspires action.
 * Learn from and collaborate with other Data Scientists, and mentor others on the team.
   
   
   

Qualifications

Minimum Qualifications / Your background:


 * 8+ Years of Experience in Data Science or related fields
 * Proficiency in SQL AND another data manipulation programming language (e.g Python, R)
 * Expertise at telling stories with data and familiarity with at least one visualization tool (e.g. Tableau, R-Shiny, Microstrategy, SAP Business Objects, Looker, etc.)
 * 5+ years of experience working with people data (e.g., survey data, HR data, psychological study data, human behavior data) in an applied setting
 * Proven ability to translate data into compelling and easy-to-understand insights, stories, and narratives that resonate with a non-technical audience
 * Experience driving projects or programs which have had proven impact on business strategy and performance through your analytics skills
 * A proven track record for crafting analysis into well-written and persuasive content
 * Experience advising, presenting to and serving as a thought partner to senior executives
   
   
   

Desirable Qualifications


 * Experience of advanced statistical methods (e.g., could include: regression, cluster analysis, HLM, social network analysis, text analysis, longitudinal methods, etc.)
 * An understanding of the SaaS business model and key metrics
   
   
   

Compensation

At Atlassian, we strive to design equitable, explainable, and competitive compensation programs. To support this goal, the baseline of our range is higher than that of the typical market range, but in turn we expect to hire most candidates near this baseline. Base pay within the range is ultimately determined by a candidate's skills, expertise, or experience. In the United States, we have three geographic pay zones. For this role, our current base pay ranges for new hires in each zone are:

Zone A: $231,600 - $308,800

Zone B: $208,400 - $277,900

Zone C: $192,200 - $256,300

This role may also be eligible for benefits, bonuses, commissions, and equity.

Please visit go.atlassian.com/payzones for more information on which locations are included in each of our geographic pay zones. However, please confirm the zone for your specific location with your recruiter.

Our Perks & Benefits

Atlassian offers a variety of perks and benefits to support you, your family and to help you engage with your local community. Our offerings include health coverage, paid volunteer days, wellness resources, and so much more. Visit go.atlassian.com/perksandbenefits to learn more.

About Atlassian

At Atlassian, we're motivated by a common goal: to unleash the potential of every team. Our software products help teams all over the planet and our solutions are designed for all types of work. Team collaboration through our tools makes what may be impossible alone, possible together.

We believe that the unique contributions of all Atlassians create our success. To ensure that our products and culture continue to incorporate everyone's perspectives and experience, we never discriminate based on race, religion, national origin, gender identity or expression, sexual orientation, age, or marital, veteran, or disability status. All your information will be kept confidential according to EEO guidelines.

To provide you the best experience, we can support with accommodations or adjustments at any stage of the recruitment process. Simply inform our Recruitment team during your conversation with them.

To learn more about our culture and hiring process, visit go.atlassian.com/crh .

description:
Our Opportunity

Work Location: Perth

Roster: Monday-Friday

As a Technology Strategy Analyst, you will play a pivotal role in shaping and executing technology strategies within our organization. Your responsibilities will span across various domains, including business case development, product performance management, software product development, executive and board reporting, program governance, acting as a Product Owner, and program strategy enablement. The primary focus of this role is to drive the successful implementation of an Artificial Intelligence (AI) program, ensuring that AI-enabled software products align with our business objectives.

The Technology Strategy Analyst will focus on an AI program that aims to create AI-enabled software products aligned with our business outcomes. You will collaborate with crossfunctional teams, drive innovation, and contribute to the organization’s growth through strategic technology initiatives.

Key Responsibilities



 * Collaborate with cross-functional teams to assess technology needs and opportunities.
 * Analyse market trends, competitive landscapes, and industry best practices.
 * Develop compelling business cases for technology investments, considering cost-benefit analyses and risk assessments.
 * Support the maintenance of a valued and prioritised backlog of opportunities.
 * Support the activities required to establish product teams including workforce and demand management, market engagement, vendor selection and onboarding.
 * Support the creation and ongoing management of program-level product performance and value management.
 * Monitor the performance of AI-enabled products, leveraging product teams and their outputs.
 * Support Steering Committee reviews and stage gate decisions.
 * Support strategic activities identifying areas for improvement, scalability, and optimization.
 * When required, act as an interim Product Owner for products.
 * Work closely with domain stakeholders, product managers, engineers, and data scientists to define product requirements.
 * Support and guide the use of patterned product development approaches throughout the product lifecycle.
 * Prepare regular reports and presentations for senior leadership and the board.
   
   
   

Qualifications And Experience



 * Bachelor’s degree in Computer Science, Engineering, Business, or a related field (Master’s preferred).
 * Proven experience in technology strategy, product management, or software development.
 * Familiarity with AI and machine learning concepts.
 * Strong analytical skills and the ability to translate data into actionable insights.
 * Excellent communication and stakeholder management skills.
   
   
   

About Us

Be part of something big. Fortescue is leading the world with our plan to decarbonise our iron ore operations, projects that harness renewable energy and the development of technology that will change our planet forever.

Our Commitment

Fortescue celebrates individual strengths and team members are encouraged to bring their whole selves to work. Our global workforce drives and promotes an inclusive culture, both within our organisation and throughout the communities we interact with. Diverse backgrounds include First Nations Peoples, people with disabilities, LGBTQ+ community, gender, neurodiverse, cultural diversity, all age groups, and those with an intersectional or multiple diverse characteristics. We encourage candidates from all backgrounds to apply.

https://fortescue.com/careers

Internal Candidates / Current Contractors please apply via Success Factors Careers Portal. For further information on how to apply please visit the Fortescue Hub.

Fortescue reserves the right to close applications early should a suitable pool of candidates be identified. Fortescue will never contact you to ask for payment of any kind, whether directly or through a third party.

Did you know someone completes a Go1 course or learning resource almost three times every second? We've grown from humble beginnings into the most diverse learning content aggregator on the planet. Our culture transcends physical walls, thriving in connections and collaboration. We embrace change as an opportunity for innovation and growth. Our pace is fast, and our goals are ambitious. If you love tackling bold challenges and growing rapidly alongside talented and humble people, you'll fit right in at Go1.

The next chapter of our growth story needs you. GO there with us.

The Data team at Go1 offers global Data and AI-centric services, including search, recommendations, content enrichment, and skills taxonomy. We collaborate with internal partners to enhance customer experiences and products. Combining Data Governance, Software, and Data Engineering expertise to provide platforms, tooling, and templates that empower our people to use data effectively. This team also captures and models core data into Data Products and promotes good data practices across Go1.

What Does a Data Engineer Do Every Day at Go1?

As a Data Engineer at Go1, you will build and maintain data products, infrastructure, and tooling for key domains and use cases. Your work will impact Analytics, Experimentation, and AI models powering Go1 products.

Key Responsibilities Include


 * Partnering with key stakeholders to define technical solutions.
 * Demonstrating excellent verbal communication skills for cross-functional team engagement.
 * Analyzing, designing, developing, and testing data processing pipelines, warehouses, marts, models, and SQL queries.
 * Scripting for orchestration, operation, and data management.
 * Managing Azure infrastructure and services.
 * Supporting Data Consumers by resolving data issues and tuning queries.
 * Conducting performance analysis and optimization of databases, SQL queries, ETL processes, and physical schemas.
 * Providing operational support, monitoring data pipelines and infrastructure, and managing CI/CD and incident management.
   
   

What will make us excited abut you


 * 3+ years experience in Data Engineering
 * Driven by requirements to acquire, manipulate, process, and demonstrate value from large datasets
 * Experienced in integrating streaming and batch data from source systems
 * Strong analytical skills with structured and unstructured datasets
 * Proficient in big data tools and batch processing technologies
 * Experienced with Spark SQL (Databricks), PySpark (Python), and scripting languages like Python and Scala
 * Proficient in SQL and data pipeline/workflow management tools

Join our team at Go1 and be at the forefront of transforming education through innovative learning solutions. Together, we can change the world. One learner at time.
